WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.430 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:03.430 --> 00:00:14.230 align:middle line:90%


00:00:14.230 --> 00:00:18.770 align:middle line:84%
>> So when I was 26, I
got a huge wake-up call.

00:00:18.770 --> 00:00:21.160 align:middle line:90%
It was stage III colon cancer.

00:00:21.160 --> 00:00:24.670 align:middle line:84%
And at that time, I was a
real estate entrepreneur.

00:00:24.670 --> 00:00:29.290 align:middle line:84%
I was just working really
hard to build a business,

00:00:29.290 --> 00:00:32.020 align:middle line:84%
acquiring rental
property, learning

00:00:32.020 --> 00:00:34.570 align:middle line:84%
how to manage properties
and run crews.

00:00:34.570 --> 00:00:38.410 align:middle line:84%
And I was just basically
going 90 miles an hour,

00:00:38.410 --> 00:00:41.790 align:middle line:84%
just a young, ambitious
guy, and also a musician.

00:00:41.790 --> 00:00:44.620 align:middle line:84%
So nights and weekends,
I was writing songs

00:00:44.620 --> 00:00:46.590 align:middle line:90%
and doing that stuff.

00:00:46.590 --> 00:00:50.960 align:middle line:84%
And so yeah, just was completely
derailed by a colon cancer

00:00:50.960 --> 00:00:51.760 align:middle line:90%
diagnosis.

00:00:51.760 --> 00:00:54.280 align:middle line:90%
I had pain in my abdomen.

00:00:54.280 --> 00:00:55.655 align:middle line:84%
And I thought,
gee, I don't know.

00:00:55.655 --> 00:00:56.455 align:middle line:90%
What's going on?

00:00:56.455 --> 00:00:57.880 align:middle line:90%
Do I have an ulcer or something?

00:00:57.880 --> 00:00:59.922 align:middle line:84%
And I just ignored it
because it wasn't that bad.

00:00:59.922 --> 00:01:00.910 align:middle line:90%
It would come and go.

00:01:00.910 --> 00:01:02.738 align:middle line:90%
Most of the time, I had no pain.

00:01:02.738 --> 00:01:04.780 align:middle line:84%
But then I would just have
these twinges everyone

00:01:04.780 --> 00:01:08.830 align:middle line:84%
once in a while, these
weird, sharp pains,

00:01:08.830 --> 00:01:14.080 align:middle line:84%
the kind where you're
like, whoa, what was that?

00:01:14.080 --> 00:01:17.800 align:middle line:84%
But over time, over the
better part of a year,

00:01:17.800 --> 00:01:19.390 align:middle line:90%
it got worse and worse.

00:01:19.390 --> 00:01:22.660 align:middle line:84%
And then eventually,
I had a colonoscopy

00:01:22.660 --> 00:01:24.370 align:middle line:84%
and they found this
golf ball-sized tumor

00:01:24.370 --> 00:01:27.310 align:middle line:84%
in my large intestine,
biopsied it sent it to the lab.

00:01:27.310 --> 00:01:32.560 align:middle line:84%
And they're like, you've
got stage II colon cancer.

00:01:32.560 --> 00:01:34.360 align:middle line:90%
This is an old person's disease.

00:01:34.360 --> 00:01:37.165 align:middle line:84%
They don't even screen for colon
cancer till you're in your 50s

00:01:37.165 --> 00:01:38.270 align:middle line:90%
and I'm 26.

00:01:38.270 --> 00:01:41.080 align:middle line:84%
So it was like,
what in the world

00:01:41.080 --> 00:01:43.150 align:middle line:90%
is happening to me right now?

00:01:43.150 --> 00:01:46.580 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:01:46.580 --> 00:01:48.540 align:middle line:90%


00:01:48.540 --> 00:01:54.390 align:middle line:84%
My wife and I had been married
for just over two years,

00:01:54.390 --> 00:01:56.670 align:middle line:90%
no kids.

00:01:56.670 --> 00:02:01.110 align:middle line:84%
We were just getting started,
just trying to build a life.

00:02:01.110 --> 00:02:04.900 align:middle line:84%
And yes, we were
talking about kids.

00:02:04.900 --> 00:02:09.660 align:middle line:84%
But yeah, this just completely
interrupted my entire life,

00:02:09.660 --> 00:02:12.090 align:middle line:84%
A. And B, it was like,
well, I don't even

00:02:12.090 --> 00:02:13.700 align:middle line:90%
know if I'm going to--

00:02:13.700 --> 00:02:14.700 align:middle line:90%
am I going to die young?

00:02:14.700 --> 00:02:17.190 align:middle line:90%
Am I going to have kids?

00:02:17.190 --> 00:02:19.210 align:middle line:84%
What's my future
going to look like?

00:02:19.210 --> 00:02:22.230 align:middle line:84%
Are my parents going to have
to bury their only child?

00:02:22.230 --> 00:02:23.740 align:middle line:84%
Is my wife going
to have to bury me,

00:02:23.740 --> 00:02:27.450 align:middle line:84%
that we've been together for
eight years, married for two?

00:02:27.450 --> 00:02:32.490 align:middle line:84%
So yeah, all these
emotions was swirling.

00:02:32.490 --> 00:02:34.460 align:middle line:90%
And it was a really scary time.

00:02:34.460 --> 00:02:41.813 align:middle line:90%


00:02:41.813 --> 00:02:43.730 align:middle line:84%
Well, the first thing
that happens when you're

00:02:43.730 --> 00:02:48.140 align:middle line:90%
diagnosed with cancer is fear.

00:02:48.140 --> 00:02:54.410 align:middle line:84%
It's a huge stress and
fear bomb in your life

00:02:54.410 --> 00:02:57.260 align:middle line:84%
because all the sudden--
your life's probably

00:02:57.260 --> 00:03:00.030 align:middle line:90%
pretty good or OK or whatever.

00:03:00.030 --> 00:03:01.228 align:middle line:90%
Maybe it's great.

00:03:01.228 --> 00:03:03.020 align:middle line:84%
And then all the sudden,
it's like, cancer,

00:03:03.020 --> 00:03:07.290 align:middle line:84%
which equals potential
death, maybe soon.

00:03:07.290 --> 00:03:11.540 align:middle line:84%
And if you know the way cancer
industry and treatment works,

00:03:11.540 --> 00:03:14.760 align:middle line:90%
it means suffering immediately.

00:03:14.760 --> 00:03:16.610 align:middle line:84%
So it's surgery,
chemo, and radiation.

00:03:16.610 --> 00:03:20.820 align:middle line:84%
These are all brutal therapies
that you will suffer,

00:03:20.820 --> 00:03:23.030 align:middle line:90%
and especially chemo.

00:03:23.030 --> 00:03:27.650 align:middle line:84%
And so yeah, instantly,
I'm afraid for my life.

00:03:27.650 --> 00:03:29.990 align:middle line:84%
And inside the cancer
industry, they really

00:03:29.990 --> 00:03:34.560 align:middle line:84%
use fear to motivate patients
just to say yes to treatment,

00:03:34.560 --> 00:03:35.630 align:middle line:90%
unfortunately.

00:03:35.630 --> 00:03:41.600 align:middle line:84%
It's just that the culture of
oncology is, to the patient,

00:03:41.600 --> 00:03:44.630 align:middle line:84%
if you don't do what I
say, you're going to die.

00:03:44.630 --> 00:03:47.420 align:middle line:84%
And a lot of times, the
patients are terminal anyway.

00:03:47.420 --> 00:03:49.190 align:middle line:90%
They're going to die anyway.

00:03:49.190 --> 00:03:50.840 align:middle line:84%
And the doctor is
not even telling them

00:03:50.840 --> 00:03:54.077 align:middle line:84%
that, oh, by the way, this
treatment can't cure you.

00:03:54.077 --> 00:03:55.660 align:middle line:84%
There's no way it's
going to cure you.

00:03:55.660 --> 00:03:59.090 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't cure anybody with
your type or your stage.

00:03:59.090 --> 00:04:02.330 align:middle line:84%
But you have to take it
or you're going to die.

00:04:02.330 --> 00:04:04.520 align:middle line:90%
So for me, that wasn't my story.

00:04:04.520 --> 00:04:06.270 align:middle line:90%
My story was slightly different.

00:04:06.270 --> 00:04:07.070 align:middle line:90%
I had surgery.

00:04:07.070 --> 00:04:08.980 align:middle line:90%
They took out this tumor.

00:04:08.980 --> 00:04:11.480 align:middle line:84%
And then they said, you need 9
to 12 months of chemotherapy.

00:04:11.480 --> 00:04:15.290 align:middle line:90%


00:04:15.290 --> 00:04:16.700 align:middle line:90%
And it's worse than we thought.

00:04:16.700 --> 00:04:18.040 align:middle line:90%
We thought it was stage II.

00:04:18.040 --> 00:04:19.720 align:middle line:90%
It's stage IIIC.

00:04:19.720 --> 00:04:26.360 align:middle line:84%
So it's one click from stage
IV, which means it's metastatic.

00:04:26.360 --> 00:04:30.320 align:middle line:84%
Colon cancer is the second
leading cause of cancer death

00:04:30.320 --> 00:04:34.400 align:middle line:84%
in the US and in many
industrialized Western nations.

00:04:34.400 --> 00:04:37.640 align:middle line:90%
So surgery doesn't cure it.

00:04:37.640 --> 00:04:41.930 align:middle line:84%
And your only hope is that
the chemotherapy will maybe

00:04:41.930 --> 00:04:45.380 align:middle line:84%
mop up the cancer stem
cells and circulating

00:04:45.380 --> 00:04:50.480 align:middle line:84%
tumor cells that are already
circulating in your body.

00:04:50.480 --> 00:04:54.710 align:middle line:90%
And what do you say to that?

00:04:54.710 --> 00:04:56.780 align:middle line:84%
I didn't know anything
about anything.

00:04:56.780 --> 00:04:59.720 align:middle line:90%
So I'm afraid I'm going to die.

00:04:59.720 --> 00:05:03.685 align:middle line:84%
And they're telling me that
if I don't do what they say,

00:05:03.685 --> 00:05:05.060 align:middle line:84%
then I'm definitely
going to die.

00:05:05.060 --> 00:05:08.532 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:05:08.532 --> 00:05:13.000 align:middle line:90%


00:05:13.000 --> 00:05:17.290 align:middle line:84%
In the very beginning of
my treatment experience,

00:05:17.290 --> 00:05:19.540 align:middle line:90%
I was rushed into surgery.

00:05:19.540 --> 00:05:23.620 align:middle line:84%
So they wanted to get me
into surgery the next day.

00:05:23.620 --> 00:05:26.620 align:middle line:84%
This is how fast the
cancer industry moves.

00:05:26.620 --> 00:05:28.052 align:middle line:90%
Patients, they get a diagnosis.

00:05:28.052 --> 00:05:29.260 align:middle line:90%
It's a whirlwind, like, what?

00:05:29.260 --> 00:05:30.430 align:middle line:90%
I have cancer now?

00:05:30.430 --> 00:05:31.260 align:middle line:90%
What's going on?

00:05:31.260 --> 00:05:33.952 align:middle line:84%
Oh, and you're going to need
to be in surgery tomorrow

00:05:33.952 --> 00:05:35.410 align:middle line:84%
and we've gotta
get this out of you

00:05:35.410 --> 00:05:37.330 align:middle line:84%
right away before it
spreads and kills you.

00:05:37.330 --> 00:05:38.510 align:middle line:90%
That's what they told me.

00:05:38.510 --> 00:05:41.080 align:middle line:84%
And so it's like, we want to
get you into surgery tomorrow.

00:05:41.080 --> 00:05:43.420 align:middle line:84%
The surgeon will call you
to set up the appointment.

00:05:43.420 --> 00:05:48.070 align:middle line:84%
And I'm just like, uh, OK
like every cancer patient.

00:05:48.070 --> 00:05:50.500 align:middle line:84%
I don't even know what's
happening to me right now.

00:05:50.500 --> 00:05:54.280 align:middle line:84%
And in my case, there was a
mix-up and they didn't call.

00:05:54.280 --> 00:05:57.445 align:middle line:84%
And then when they finally
did two days later--

00:05:57.445 --> 00:06:00.845 align:middle line:84%
because this was two
days before Christmas,

00:06:00.845 --> 00:06:01.720 align:middle line:90%
when I was diagnosed.

00:06:01.720 --> 00:06:05.620 align:middle line:84%
I'm like, great, awesome
Christmas this is going to be.

00:06:05.620 --> 00:06:06.890 align:middle line:90%
And they finally called.

00:06:06.890 --> 00:06:09.140 align:middle line:84%
And I said, look,
can we wait a week?

00:06:09.140 --> 00:06:12.560 align:middle line:84%
Because I don't want to be in
the hospital over Christmas.

00:06:12.560 --> 00:06:14.380 align:middle line:90%
It's already depressing enough.

00:06:14.380 --> 00:06:16.990 align:middle line:84%
Can I at least not be in
the hospital on Christmas?

00:06:16.990 --> 00:06:18.370 align:middle line:90%
So we postponed it a week.

00:06:18.370 --> 00:06:21.250 align:middle line:84%
But still, a week is
not much time either.

00:06:21.250 --> 00:06:24.070 align:middle line:90%
A week-- so I have surgery.

00:06:24.070 --> 00:06:26.713 align:middle line:84%
They take out a third
of my large intestine.

00:06:26.713 --> 00:06:27.880 align:middle line:90%
And they take out the tumor.

00:06:27.880 --> 00:06:30.160 align:middle line:84%
And they realize that it's
spread to my lymph nodes

00:06:30.160 --> 00:06:31.452 align:middle line:90%
and it's worse than we thought.

00:06:31.452 --> 00:06:33.730 align:middle line:90%
It's stage IIIC, not stage II.

00:06:33.730 --> 00:06:39.940 align:middle line:84%
And things were looking
worse and worse.

00:06:39.940 --> 00:06:43.330 align:middle line:84%
It was just more bad news,
like, oh, now you need chemo.

00:06:43.330 --> 00:06:46.120 align:middle line:84%
You need 9 to 12
months of chemotherapy.

00:06:46.120 --> 00:06:51.653 align:middle line:84%
And the idea of chemotherapy
didn't make sense to me.

00:06:51.653 --> 00:06:54.070 align:middle line:84%
Even though I'd never had any
friends or family members go

00:06:54.070 --> 00:06:58.690 align:middle line:84%
through cancer, just
the idea of poisoning

00:06:58.690 --> 00:07:03.293 align:middle line:84%
me to get healthier, that I'm
going to poison myself back

00:07:03.293 --> 00:07:05.710 align:middle line:84%
to health or that you're going
to poison me back to health

00:07:05.710 --> 00:07:08.127 align:middle line:84%
and I'm going to get really,
really sick but then somehow,

00:07:08.127 --> 00:07:10.690 align:middle line:84%
it's going to make me better,
I couldn't make sense of it.

00:07:10.690 --> 00:07:15.640 align:middle line:84%
And I'm a very
rational, intuitive guy,

00:07:15.640 --> 00:07:18.550 align:middle line:84%
which sounds like a
contradiction, sort of.

00:07:18.550 --> 00:07:23.600 align:middle line:90%
But I couldn't rationalize it.

00:07:23.600 --> 00:07:25.580 align:middle line:90%
It just didn't make sense.

00:07:25.580 --> 00:07:30.760 align:middle line:84%
And so I had this nagging
problem with chemo.

00:07:30.760 --> 00:07:33.580 align:middle line:90%
And I was also deeply insecure.

00:07:33.580 --> 00:07:35.480 align:middle line:90%
I was a deeply insecure guy.

00:07:35.480 --> 00:07:39.250 align:middle line:84%
And so the thought
of myself being

00:07:39.250 --> 00:07:46.180 align:middle line:84%
reduced to this emaciated,
bald, yellow skin--

00:07:46.180 --> 00:07:56.930 align:middle line:84%
just a cancer patient, that
was just an awful feeling.

00:07:56.930 --> 00:08:01.160 align:middle line:90%


00:08:01.160 --> 00:08:05.780 align:middle line:84%
And so I had an
aversion to it just

00:08:05.780 --> 00:08:08.830 align:middle line:90%
from being really insecure.

00:08:08.830 --> 00:08:12.000 align:middle line:90%
I didn't want to become that.

00:08:12.000 --> 00:08:16.820 align:middle line:84%
And so I didn't know
what to do, though.

00:08:16.820 --> 00:08:19.100 align:middle line:84%
And my wife and I go home
and we pray about it.

00:08:19.100 --> 00:08:21.267 align:middle line:84%
I'm like, God, if there's
another way, just show me.

00:08:21.267 --> 00:08:22.430 align:middle line:90%
I don't know what to do.

00:08:22.430 --> 00:08:24.350 align:middle line:84%
And this just
doesn't seem right.

00:08:24.350 --> 00:08:27.140 align:middle line:84%
I'm just reaching
out, like, help.

00:08:27.140 --> 00:08:30.500 align:middle line:84%
And I get a book that comes
to me from a man in Alaska who

00:08:30.500 --> 00:08:31.610 align:middle line:90%
knew my dad.

00:08:31.610 --> 00:08:34.289 align:middle line:84%
Sends me a book that
was written by a man who

00:08:34.289 --> 00:08:38.960 align:middle line:84%
had healed his own colon cancer
with diet, radical diet change,

00:08:38.960 --> 00:08:41.929 align:middle line:90%
raw food, tons of carrot juice.

00:08:41.929 --> 00:08:44.630 align:middle line:90%
And his cancer healed.

00:08:44.630 --> 00:08:47.600 align:middle line:84%
So it wasn't a quick fix or
a magic bullet or whatever.

00:08:47.600 --> 00:08:53.480 align:middle line:84%
It was just a very deliberate,
systematic radical diet

00:08:53.480 --> 00:08:54.860 align:middle line:90%
and life change.

00:08:54.860 --> 00:08:57.170 align:middle line:84%
And I'm reading this book
and I'm like, this is it.

00:08:57.170 --> 00:08:58.970 align:middle line:84%
I asked for something
and this book came.

00:08:58.970 --> 00:09:00.590 align:middle line:90%
This is it.

00:09:00.590 --> 00:09:03.950 align:middle line:84%
I'm just going to believe this
is the answer to my prayer.

00:09:03.950 --> 00:09:09.200 align:middle line:84%
I can chalk it up or write
it off as a coincidence

00:09:09.200 --> 00:09:13.370 align:middle line:84%
or I can just choose to
believe, exercise my faith

00:09:13.370 --> 00:09:14.690 align:middle line:90%
and be like, OK.

00:09:14.690 --> 00:09:16.220 align:middle line:90%
And so that's what I did.

00:09:16.220 --> 00:09:17.678 align:middle line:90%
And I was excited about it.

00:09:17.678 --> 00:09:18.970 align:middle line:90%
I was reading this guy's story.

00:09:18.970 --> 00:09:19.820 align:middle line:84%
I was like, man,
this is amazing.

00:09:19.820 --> 00:09:21.112 align:middle line:90%
This makes so much sense to me.

00:09:21.112 --> 00:09:25.710 align:middle line:84%
And in 2004, nobody was talking
about the raw food diet.

00:09:25.710 --> 00:09:26.735 align:middle line:90%
It was weird.

00:09:26.735 --> 00:09:27.610 align:middle line:90%
That was for weirdos.

00:09:27.610 --> 00:09:30.350 align:middle line:90%


00:09:30.350 --> 00:09:32.072 align:middle line:84%
I even worked at
a Wild Oats, which

00:09:32.072 --> 00:09:34.280 align:middle line:84%
got bought out by Whole
Foods, and never heard anyone

00:09:34.280 --> 00:09:36.740 align:middle line:84%
mention a raw food diet when
I worked there in college.

00:09:36.740 --> 00:09:39.620 align:middle line:90%
So it was even weird to me.

00:09:39.620 --> 00:09:42.200 align:middle line:84%
But it made sense, because
the premise is like,

00:09:42.200 --> 00:09:44.150 align:middle line:84%
hey, let's stop eating
all this fast food

00:09:44.150 --> 00:09:47.510 align:middle line:84%
and junk food and processed
food, all this garbage and way

00:09:47.510 --> 00:09:49.550 align:middle line:84%
too much meat and
dairy, and let's

00:09:49.550 --> 00:09:51.350 align:middle line:84%
go back to this really
simple diet of food

00:09:51.350 --> 00:09:54.230 align:middle line:84%
straight from the
earth, unadulterated,

00:09:54.230 --> 00:09:59.040 align:middle line:84%
organic fruits and vegetables
in their natural state.

00:09:59.040 --> 00:10:00.880 align:middle line:84%
So I'm like, I've
never done this.

00:10:00.880 --> 00:10:02.990 align:middle line:90%
This makes sense.

00:10:02.990 --> 00:10:05.910 align:middle line:84%
And it sounds a lot
better than chemo.

00:10:05.910 --> 00:10:08.200 align:middle line:90%
So OK, I'm doing it.

00:10:08.200 --> 00:10:09.950 align:middle line:84%
I call my wife and I
was excited about it.

00:10:09.950 --> 00:10:12.480 align:middle line:90%
And she was not excited.

00:10:12.480 --> 00:10:14.510 align:middle line:84%
She grew up in a very
conventionally-minded

00:10:14.510 --> 00:10:15.310 align:middle line:90%
household.

00:10:15.310 --> 00:10:16.970 align:middle line:84%
They went to the
doctor for everything.

00:10:16.970 --> 00:10:20.210 align:middle line:90%
And she couldn't understand it.

00:10:20.210 --> 00:10:21.410 align:middle line:90%
I grew up in--

00:10:21.410 --> 00:10:25.970 align:middle line:84%
my mom was a natural health
nut kind of lady and shopped

00:10:25.970 --> 00:10:29.600 align:middle line:84%
at hole-in-the-wall
health food stores.

00:10:29.600 --> 00:10:33.020 align:middle line:84%
And we always had little, weird
supplements and food products

00:10:33.020 --> 00:10:37.460 align:middle line:84%
and stuff that my friends were
like, what is this, something

00:10:37.460 --> 00:10:41.090 align:middle line:90%
with kelp in it in 1990.

00:10:41.090 --> 00:10:44.932 align:middle line:84%
So anyway, the point is
I was comfortable with it

00:10:44.932 --> 00:10:45.732 align:middle line:90%
and it made sense.

00:10:45.732 --> 00:10:51.440 align:middle line:84%
So the next thing that happened
was I had all these family

00:10:51.440 --> 00:10:53.150 align:middle line:84%
members start to
call me and tell me

00:10:53.150 --> 00:10:56.642 align:middle line:84%
that I was making a
mistake I was like,

00:10:56.642 --> 00:10:58.100 align:middle line:84%
well, I prayed and
I got this book.

00:10:58.100 --> 00:11:00.020 align:middle line:90%
And I'm like, this is it.

00:11:00.020 --> 00:11:01.738 align:middle line:90%
I had so much clarity.

00:11:01.738 --> 00:11:03.530 align:middle line:84%
And then all the sudden,
everyone around me

00:11:03.530 --> 00:11:06.780 align:middle line:90%
is like, no, no, do not do that.

00:11:06.780 --> 00:11:08.750 align:middle line:84%
I know someone who did
alternative therapies

00:11:08.750 --> 00:11:13.795 align:middle line:84%
and they died or don't
you think if there

00:11:13.795 --> 00:11:15.170 align:middle line:84%
was something that
worked better,

00:11:15.170 --> 00:11:18.180 align:middle line:90%
the doctors would know about it?

00:11:18.180 --> 00:11:21.380 align:middle line:84%
And I'm like, I don't know
how to answer these questions.

00:11:21.380 --> 00:11:25.710 align:middle line:84%
I've only read the first
couple chapters of this book.

00:11:25.710 --> 00:11:26.510 align:middle line:90%
I don't even know.

00:11:26.510 --> 00:11:31.130 align:middle line:84%
So then all the sudden, the fear
is back, the fear, the doubt,

00:11:31.130 --> 00:11:32.060 align:middle line:90%
the anxiety.

00:11:32.060 --> 00:11:35.720 align:middle line:90%
It's all back and present.

00:11:35.720 --> 00:11:41.720 align:middle line:84%
And it was very tough
because I realized

00:11:41.720 --> 00:11:44.240 align:middle line:84%
my mom supported me,
but beyond my mom

00:11:44.240 --> 00:11:48.680 align:middle line:84%
at that time, everyone else
who loved me didn't understand.

00:11:48.680 --> 00:11:52.850 align:middle line:84%
And so they couldn't support
me because it was just such

00:11:52.850 --> 00:11:57.830 align:middle line:84%
a radical idea that
they just couldn't--

00:11:57.830 --> 00:12:01.580 align:middle line:84%
it was as weird to them
as chemo was weird to me.

00:12:01.580 --> 00:12:04.190 align:middle line:90%
And I realized I was alone.

00:12:04.190 --> 00:12:06.830 align:middle line:90%
And that was scary.

00:12:06.830 --> 00:12:11.400 align:middle line:84%
And so in order to appease
the people around me,

00:12:11.400 --> 00:12:14.150 align:middle line:84%
I agreed to go
see an oncologist.

00:12:14.150 --> 00:12:16.140 align:middle line:84%
They were saying, well,
will you please just

00:12:16.140 --> 00:12:18.680 align:middle line:84%
go meet with them, hear
what they have to say?

00:12:18.680 --> 00:12:21.050 align:middle line:84%
And I'm like, OK,
OK, OK, I'll go.

00:12:21.050 --> 00:12:23.780 align:middle line:84%
But by the way, I had
converted to a raw food diet

00:12:23.780 --> 00:12:26.240 align:middle line:84%
overnight, went out,
where can I buy a juicer?

00:12:26.240 --> 00:12:27.285 align:middle line:90%
Who sells them?

00:12:27.285 --> 00:12:29.660 align:middle line:84%
Bought the juicer, loaded up
on raw fruits of vegetables,

00:12:29.660 --> 00:12:30.460 align:middle line:90%
giant--

00:12:30.460 --> 00:12:33.680 align:middle line:84%
I realized, whoa, they sell
these 20-pound bags of organic

00:12:33.680 --> 00:12:36.860 align:middle line:84%
juicing carrots,
carrots for making--

00:12:36.860 --> 00:12:38.490 align:middle line:90%
I'm like, this is amazing.

00:12:38.490 --> 00:12:39.380 align:middle line:90%
I had no idea.

00:12:39.380 --> 00:12:44.270 align:middle line:84%
So I loaded up on this produce,
started on the raw food diet.

00:12:44.270 --> 00:12:46.610 align:middle line:84%
And then again, OK,
I'll see the oncologist.

00:12:46.610 --> 00:12:49.020 align:middle line:90%
So we go to the clinic.

00:12:49.020 --> 00:12:51.140 align:middle line:90%
And it's full of people.

00:12:51.140 --> 00:12:54.950 align:middle line:84%
They're all twice my
age, three times my age.

00:12:54.950 --> 00:12:56.450 align:middle line:90%
I was a rock and roll dude.

00:12:56.450 --> 00:12:58.190 align:middle line:84%
I was playing in
bands, writing songs.

00:12:58.190 --> 00:13:00.680 align:middle line:84%
I had shaggy hair and
a handlebar mustache.

00:13:00.680 --> 00:13:04.280 align:middle line:84%
And I was just like,
what am I doing here?

00:13:04.280 --> 00:13:05.450 align:middle line:90%
I don't even belong here.

00:13:05.450 --> 00:13:09.410 align:middle line:90%


00:13:09.410 --> 00:13:11.480 align:middle line:90%
And the TV is on.

00:13:11.480 --> 00:13:13.370 align:middle line:90%
And out comes Jack Lalanne.

00:13:13.370 --> 00:13:17.390 align:middle line:84%
Jack Lalanne is on the morning
show in the tiny, little window

00:13:17.390 --> 00:13:21.243 align:middle line:84%
of time that I'm sitting in
the oncologist's waiting room.

00:13:21.243 --> 00:13:22.910 align:middle line:84%
And he comes out and
he starts going off

00:13:22.910 --> 00:13:25.033 align:middle line:84%
about nutrition and natural
therapies and healing

00:13:25.033 --> 00:13:26.450 align:middle line:84%
and the reasons
why we're all sick

00:13:26.450 --> 00:13:28.992 align:middle line:84%
is because we're eating all this
junk food and processed food

00:13:28.992 --> 00:13:33.230 align:middle line:84%
and if man made
it, don't eat it.

00:13:33.230 --> 00:13:37.130 align:middle line:84%
And I'm like, man, I
can't believe this is--

00:13:37.130 --> 00:13:38.868 align:middle line:90%
he's on the TV right now.

00:13:38.868 --> 00:13:41.160 align:middle line:84%
There's no way this is not--
this is not a coincidence.

00:13:41.160 --> 00:13:43.400 align:middle line:90%
This cannot be a coincidence.

00:13:43.400 --> 00:13:45.780 align:middle line:84%
And I was like, can you
believe this is on right now,

00:13:45.780 --> 00:13:46.580 align:middle line:90%
to my wife.

00:13:46.580 --> 00:13:50.360 align:middle line:84%
And she's like, yeah,
it's pretty weird.

00:13:50.360 --> 00:13:52.700 align:middle line:84%
So we go back and
see the oncologist.

00:13:52.700 --> 00:13:55.070 align:middle line:84%
And he gives me this
really standard pitch.

00:13:55.070 --> 00:13:57.450 align:middle line:84%
You've got stage
III colon cancer.

00:13:57.450 --> 00:14:01.220 align:middle line:84%
You've got about a 60% chance of
living 5 years with treatment.

00:14:01.220 --> 00:14:07.070 align:middle line:84%
And I'm thinking, 60%
chance of living 5 years?

00:14:07.070 --> 00:14:09.620 align:middle line:84%
That's barely better
than a coin toss.

00:14:09.620 --> 00:14:10.635 align:middle line:90%
What if he's wrong?

00:14:10.635 --> 00:14:11.435 align:middle line:90%
What if it's worse?

00:14:11.435 --> 00:14:14.270 align:middle line:90%


00:14:14.270 --> 00:14:17.210 align:middle line:84%
So it didn't inspire
any confidence.

00:14:17.210 --> 00:14:20.480 align:middle line:84%
And I asked him about
the raw food diet.

00:14:20.480 --> 00:14:22.310 align:middle line:84%
And he said, no,
you can't do it.

00:14:22.310 --> 00:14:24.206 align:middle line:90%
It'll fight the chemo.

00:14:24.206 --> 00:14:26.270 align:middle line:90%
And I was like, that's weird.

00:14:26.270 --> 00:14:28.280 align:middle line:84%
And I never asked
him what he meant,

00:14:28.280 --> 00:14:31.142 align:middle line:90%
but it was a weird thing to say.

00:14:31.142 --> 00:14:32.600 align:middle line:84%
I found out later
that the raw food

00:14:32.600 --> 00:14:36.890 align:middle line:84%
diet is such a powerful
detoxification and cleansing

00:14:36.890 --> 00:14:40.490 align:middle line:84%
diet that when you're trying
to do raw foods and chemo,

00:14:40.490 --> 00:14:43.502 align:middle line:84%
your body kicks the
chemo out a lot faster

00:14:43.502 --> 00:14:45.960 align:middle line:84%
and it doesn't really do as
much damage, which sounds good;

00:14:45.960 --> 00:14:49.580 align:middle line:84%
but to them, they want it to
do as much damage as possible.

00:14:49.580 --> 00:14:53.480 align:middle line:90%
So they don't work together.

00:14:53.480 --> 00:14:58.070 align:middle line:84%
And they're also afraid that
any bacteria on raw food

00:14:58.070 --> 00:15:01.520 align:middle line:84%
is going to harm you
because they've destroyed

00:15:01.520 --> 00:15:04.280 align:middle line:90%
your immune system with chemo.

00:15:04.280 --> 00:15:08.030 align:middle line:84%
And so now, the
bacteria on an apple

00:15:08.030 --> 00:15:09.890 align:middle line:84%
might cause a
problem in your body.

00:15:09.890 --> 00:15:12.450 align:middle line:90%


00:15:12.450 --> 00:15:14.943 align:middle line:90%
I learned all that later.

00:15:14.943 --> 00:15:16.610 align:middle line:84%
We asked him about
alternative therapies

00:15:16.610 --> 00:15:21.210 align:middle line:90%
and he said, no, there are none.

00:15:21.210 --> 00:15:23.300 align:middle line:84%
And if you don't do
chemotherapy, you're insane.

00:15:23.300 --> 00:15:26.300 align:middle line:90%


00:15:26.300 --> 00:15:31.850 align:middle line:84%
And that moment, just
a tidal wave of fear

00:15:31.850 --> 00:15:36.380 align:middle line:84%
just smashed me, it was like,
smashed me on the rocks.

00:15:36.380 --> 00:15:41.870 align:middle line:90%
And when you're under stress--

00:15:41.870 --> 00:15:43.850 align:middle line:90%
fear is a stress emotion.

00:15:43.850 --> 00:15:45.470 align:middle line:84%
When you're under
stress, your body

00:15:45.470 --> 00:15:46.922 align:middle line:90%
responds with fight or flight.

00:15:46.922 --> 00:15:48.380 align:middle line:84%
And the fight or
flight response is

00:15:48.380 --> 00:15:52.010 align:middle line:84%
it starts pumping hormones,
adrenaline and cortisol.

00:15:52.010 --> 00:15:56.540 align:middle line:84%
And those hormones make a
lot of physiological changes

00:15:56.540 --> 00:15:57.525 align:middle line:90%
in the body.

00:15:57.525 --> 00:15:59.150 align:middle line:84%
There are these
physiological reactions

00:15:59.150 --> 00:16:00.440 align:middle line:90%
that happen in the body.

00:16:00.440 --> 00:16:04.760 align:middle line:84%
And one of them is your
brain chemistry changes.

00:16:04.760 --> 00:16:06.320 align:middle line:90%
You think very differently.

00:16:06.320 --> 00:16:09.230 align:middle line:84%
And parts of your brain
actually shut off, your ability

00:16:09.230 --> 00:16:13.190 align:middle line:84%
to think rationally and
logically, analytically,

00:16:13.190 --> 00:16:14.600 align:middle line:90%
shut off.

00:16:14.600 --> 00:16:17.600 align:middle line:84%
And the part of your
brain that lights up

00:16:17.600 --> 00:16:21.170 align:middle line:84%
is the part that's really
wired for survival.

00:16:21.170 --> 00:16:23.030 align:middle line:90%
It's fight or flight.

00:16:23.030 --> 00:16:29.840 align:middle line:84%
And that part is very
irrational and impulsive.

00:16:29.840 --> 00:16:32.330 align:middle line:90%
And so even your memory--

00:16:32.330 --> 00:16:35.360 align:middle line:84%
your memory stops recording when
you're under extreme stress,

00:16:35.360 --> 00:16:37.490 align:middle line:84%
which is why you hear
testimonies from people all

00:16:37.490 --> 00:16:40.070 align:middle line:84%
the time that when they're
in a traumatic event,

00:16:40.070 --> 00:16:42.010 align:middle line:90%
a fight or life-threatening--

00:16:42.010 --> 00:16:45.300 align:middle line:84%
and they're asked, can
you tell us what happened,

00:16:45.300 --> 00:16:49.080 align:middle line:84%
a lot of times, they're like, I
don't even know what happened.

00:16:49.080 --> 00:16:50.318 align:middle line:90%
It's like I blacked out.

00:16:50.318 --> 00:16:51.860 align:middle line:84%
Because the stress
hormones interfere

00:16:51.860 --> 00:16:52.943 align:middle line:90%
with your brain chemistry.

00:16:52.943 --> 00:16:58.710 align:middle line:84%
So I'm sitting there and I'm
in this hyper fear/anxiety

00:16:58.710 --> 00:16:59.510 align:middle line:90%
situation.

00:16:59.510 --> 00:17:03.440 align:middle line:84%
And he's belittling me and
just talking down to me

00:17:03.440 --> 00:17:06.770 align:middle line:84%
and just essentially
saying, if you

00:17:06.770 --> 00:17:09.800 align:middle line:84%
don't do what I'm telling you
to do, you're going to die.

00:17:09.800 --> 00:17:13.069 align:middle line:90%
And it's all blurry.

00:17:13.069 --> 00:17:16.940 align:middle line:84%
And something he said
just pokes through.

00:17:16.940 --> 00:17:19.601 align:middle line:84%
And he says, blah, blah, blah,
and I'm not telling you this

00:17:19.601 --> 00:17:20.809 align:middle line:90%
because I need your business.

00:17:20.809 --> 00:17:23.930 align:middle line:90%


00:17:23.930 --> 00:17:26.000 align:middle line:90%
And I was like, wait a minute.

00:17:26.000 --> 00:17:28.580 align:middle line:90%
This sounds like a sales pitch.

00:17:28.580 --> 00:17:31.880 align:middle line:84%
I was in sales and this guy's
doing the push away technique

00:17:31.880 --> 00:17:33.240 align:middle line:90%
on me right now.

00:17:33.240 --> 00:17:35.918 align:middle line:84%
It's a sales technique, like,
I don't need your business.

00:17:35.918 --> 00:17:37.460 align:middle line:84%
And then you're
like, oh, well, maybe

00:17:37.460 --> 00:17:40.480 align:middle line:90%
I should work with you, then.

00:17:40.480 --> 00:17:44.130 align:middle line:90%
And I'm thinking, man, business.

00:17:44.130 --> 00:17:46.610 align:middle line:90%
This is a business.

00:17:46.610 --> 00:17:47.630 align:middle line:90%
This is a business.

00:17:47.630 --> 00:17:51.950 align:middle line:84%
And this guy is actually
giving me a pitch right now.

00:17:51.950 --> 00:17:56.480 align:middle line:84%
And so even though I had
these little epiphanies

00:17:56.480 --> 00:18:02.510 align:middle line:84%
and was getting these
clues at our meeting,

00:18:02.510 --> 00:18:04.670 align:middle line:84%
the fear was so
strong and so powerful

00:18:04.670 --> 00:18:07.190 align:middle line:84%
and the anxiety
that like a robot,

00:18:07.190 --> 00:18:12.350 align:middle line:84%
I basically finished our meeting
and walked straight to the desk

00:18:12.350 --> 00:18:14.870 align:middle line:84%
and made an appointment
to start chemo,

00:18:14.870 --> 00:18:17.750 align:middle line:84%
to get a port put in in a
few weeks and start chemo.

00:18:17.750 --> 00:18:20.870 align:middle line:84%
I walked into the
oncology clinic

00:18:20.870 --> 00:18:25.940 align:middle line:84%
confident in what I was doing
and I walked out terrified.

00:18:25.940 --> 00:18:27.710 align:middle line:84%
And a lot of cancer
clinics are like that.

00:18:27.710 --> 00:18:30.170 align:middle line:90%
It's like a fear factory.

00:18:30.170 --> 00:18:33.470 align:middle line:84%
And so I made a
fear-based decision.

00:18:33.470 --> 00:18:35.990 align:middle line:90%


00:18:35.990 --> 00:18:37.550 align:middle line:84%
I'm afraid I'm
going to die, so OK.

00:18:37.550 --> 00:18:40.700 align:middle line:84%
I guess I got to do
chemo if I want to live.

00:18:40.700 --> 00:18:45.150 align:middle line:84%
And my wife and I walked to
her car and just cried, man.

00:18:45.150 --> 00:18:47.760 align:middle line:84%
We were just so
upset and scared.

00:18:47.760 --> 00:18:49.770 align:middle line:90%
And we held hands in her car.

00:18:49.770 --> 00:18:53.270 align:middle line:84%
And I just remember us
sitting there just choking

00:18:53.270 --> 00:19:00.710 align:middle line:84%
through a prayer and
just in true desperation

00:19:00.710 --> 00:19:05.310 align:middle line:84%
because my faith had
just been shattered.

00:19:05.310 --> 00:19:06.543 align:middle line:90%
My confidence was shattered.

00:19:06.543 --> 00:19:08.210 align:middle line:84%
I'd been on the raw
food diet for a week

00:19:08.210 --> 00:19:09.330 align:middle line:90%
and I was feeling good.

00:19:09.330 --> 00:19:10.490 align:middle line:90%
I really was.

00:19:10.490 --> 00:19:14.200 align:middle line:90%
But everything just got--

00:19:14.200 --> 00:19:15.950 align:middle line:84%
we used an expression
when I was in sales.

00:19:15.950 --> 00:19:18.840 align:middle line:84%
It was called blowing
up the island.

00:19:18.840 --> 00:19:20.767 align:middle line:84%
And that's basically
what it felt like.

00:19:20.767 --> 00:19:22.100 align:middle line:90%
This guy just blew up my island.

00:19:22.100 --> 00:19:24.690 align:middle line:84%
And I was like, I
don't know what to do.

00:19:24.690 --> 00:19:29.090 align:middle line:84%
And so I was fortunate
to have a few weeks

00:19:29.090 --> 00:19:30.620 align:middle line:90%
before the chemo would start.

00:19:30.620 --> 00:19:32.690 align:middle line:84%
So it wasn't like, you
got to start tomorrow.

00:19:32.690 --> 00:19:35.270 align:middle line:84%
Because they knew I still
had to recover from surgery.

00:19:35.270 --> 00:19:38.000 align:middle line:90%
I'm still had fresh scar.

00:19:38.000 --> 00:19:41.740 align:middle line:84%
So in that time, I
thought back through--

00:19:41.740 --> 00:19:45.710 align:middle line:84%
I was just praying a
lot and thinking a lot.

00:19:45.710 --> 00:19:48.800 align:middle line:84%
And I was thinking about,
why do I have cancer

00:19:48.800 --> 00:19:53.360 align:middle line:84%
and thinking about
the weird stuff

00:19:53.360 --> 00:19:55.705 align:middle line:84%
that the oncologist said to
me and the way treated me.

00:19:55.705 --> 00:19:57.080 align:middle line:84%
And I was thinking
about the book

00:19:57.080 --> 00:19:58.850 align:middle line:90%
that came to me from Alaska.

00:19:58.850 --> 00:20:02.510 align:middle line:84%
And I was thinking about Jack
Lalanne on the TV in the cancer

00:20:02.510 --> 00:20:03.663 align:middle line:90%
clinic, all these things.

00:20:03.663 --> 00:20:05.330 align:middle line:84%
And I'm trying to
piece it all together.

00:20:05.330 --> 00:20:09.180 align:middle line:90%


00:20:09.180 --> 00:20:10.480 align:middle line:90%
And I wished I--

00:20:10.480 --> 00:20:18.140 align:middle line:84%
I just so desperately wanted
an option that wasn't scary.

00:20:18.140 --> 00:20:19.820 align:middle line:90%
And I didn't have one.

00:20:19.820 --> 00:20:22.493 align:middle line:84%
On one hand, I had
the chemo train

00:20:22.493 --> 00:20:23.660 align:middle line:90%
that everybody's getting on.

00:20:23.660 --> 00:20:27.330 align:middle line:84%
It's state-of-the-art, luxury
train with the most comfortable

00:20:27.330 --> 00:20:31.560 align:middle line:90%
chairs you've ever sat on.

00:20:31.560 --> 00:20:35.190 align:middle line:84%
And everything seems
beautiful and modern.

00:20:35.190 --> 00:20:37.620 align:middle line:84%
And everyone's cheering
you on and supporting you

00:20:37.620 --> 00:20:39.615 align:middle line:84%
and they're running
races for you and stuff.

00:20:39.615 --> 00:20:43.510 align:middle line:90%


00:20:43.510 --> 00:20:45.030 align:middle line:84%
But yeah, OK, it
seems really great.

00:20:45.030 --> 00:20:47.287 align:middle line:84%
But then there's
immediate suffering.

00:20:47.287 --> 00:20:49.620 align:middle line:84%
You're going to suffer as
soon as you get on that train.

00:20:49.620 --> 00:20:52.350 align:middle line:84%
And once you get on that train,
it's really hard to get off.

00:20:52.350 --> 00:20:54.563 align:middle line:84%
And then well, what
happens-- where's it going?

00:20:54.563 --> 00:20:55.980 align:middle line:84%
At the end of the
line, am I going

00:20:55.980 --> 00:21:00.210 align:middle line:90%
to be better or worse or dead?

00:21:00.210 --> 00:21:02.620 align:middle line:90%
And so there's that option.

00:21:02.620 --> 00:21:04.860 align:middle line:84%
And then the other option
is me going into the jungle

00:21:04.860 --> 00:21:09.600 align:middle line:84%
alone, just hacking my way
through the jungle, no help,

00:21:09.600 --> 00:21:11.160 align:middle line:90%
in the dark.

00:21:11.160 --> 00:21:14.680 align:middle line:90%
And that option was scary.

00:21:14.680 --> 00:21:18.810 align:middle line:90%
I had two scary options.

00:21:18.810 --> 00:21:24.360 align:middle line:90%
And so fear was a big factor--

00:21:24.360 --> 00:21:27.120 align:middle line:90%
fear factor.

00:21:27.120 --> 00:21:32.150 align:middle line:84%
And I just wished one of
them was easy and exciting.

00:21:32.150 --> 00:21:33.900 align:middle line:84%
And I think that's
what we all want, like,

00:21:33.900 --> 00:21:35.250 align:middle line:90%
what's the easy path?

00:21:35.250 --> 00:21:37.380 align:middle line:90%
And neither of them were easy.

00:21:37.380 --> 00:21:40.140 align:middle line:84%
But I knew that the
jungle path that I

00:21:40.140 --> 00:21:43.260 align:middle line:84%
had to hack my way
through alone was the path

00:21:43.260 --> 00:21:45.660 align:middle line:90%
that God had shown me.

00:21:45.660 --> 00:21:46.980 align:middle line:90%
I asked for another way.

00:21:46.980 --> 00:21:50.190 align:middle line:84%
And he's like, OK,
here's another way

00:21:50.190 --> 00:21:51.780 align:middle line:90%
if you want to take it.

00:21:51.780 --> 00:21:54.270 align:middle line:84%
And that was a
moment for me that

00:21:54.270 --> 00:21:58.980 align:middle line:84%
was a really critical faith
moment, where I realized,

00:21:58.980 --> 00:22:00.962 align:middle line:90%
I have to choose.

00:22:00.962 --> 00:22:01.920 align:middle line:90%
I don't want to choose.

00:22:01.920 --> 00:22:03.295 align:middle line:84%
I wish someone
would just tell me

00:22:03.295 --> 00:22:06.450 align:middle line:90%
what to do and choose for me.

00:22:06.450 --> 00:22:08.100 align:middle line:84%
That's what most
cancer patients do.

00:22:08.100 --> 00:22:11.370 align:middle line:84%
They just give all of their
authority to the doctor

00:22:11.370 --> 00:22:13.440 align:middle line:84%
and just say, just
tell me what to do,

00:22:13.440 --> 00:22:15.660 align:middle line:90%
and you just choose for me.

00:22:15.660 --> 00:22:18.960 align:middle line:84%
And they've abdicated all
of their responsibilities

00:22:18.960 --> 00:22:21.530 align:middle line:84%
to someone who probably won't
remember their name if they

00:22:21.530 --> 00:22:23.250 align:middle line:90%
saw them in the grocery store.

00:22:23.250 --> 00:22:26.270 align:middle line:90%


00:22:26.270 --> 00:22:28.950 align:middle line:84%
And then there was the
full responsibility,

00:22:28.950 --> 00:22:31.860 align:middle line:90%
it all depends on me road.

00:22:31.860 --> 00:22:35.220 align:middle line:84%
And if I screw up, if I
do this wrong and I die,

00:22:35.220 --> 00:22:42.090 align:middle line:84%
I look like a fool and I
become the cautionary tale.

00:22:42.090 --> 00:22:45.570 align:middle line:90%
And that was scary.

00:22:45.570 --> 00:22:49.870 align:middle line:84%
And so it was like, OK, this
is the test of my faith right

00:22:49.870 --> 00:22:50.670 align:middle line:90%
here.

00:22:50.670 --> 00:22:53.370 align:middle line:90%
If I step into this path--

00:22:53.370 --> 00:22:55.043 align:middle line:84%
God, if you gave
me this path, I'm

00:22:55.043 --> 00:22:57.210 align:middle line:84%
just going to have to trust
you to see me through it

00:22:57.210 --> 00:23:02.400 align:middle line:84%
because I can't even see
two feet in front of me.

00:23:02.400 --> 00:23:04.350 align:middle line:84%
I don't know what
is even in there.

00:23:04.350 --> 00:23:07.290 align:middle line:84%
I don't know where
this is going at all.

00:23:07.290 --> 00:23:08.780 align:middle line:90%
But I had to take it.

00:23:08.780 --> 00:23:10.770 align:middle line:90%
The chemo appointment shows up.

00:23:10.770 --> 00:23:12.660 align:middle line:90%
The day arrives.

00:23:12.660 --> 00:23:15.840 align:middle line:84%
And every day
approaching that day, I

00:23:15.840 --> 00:23:17.940 align:middle line:84%
got more and more
stressed and nervous

00:23:17.940 --> 00:23:20.092 align:middle line:90%
and like, what am I going to do?

00:23:20.092 --> 00:23:21.300 align:middle line:90%
And finally, the day arrives.

00:23:21.300 --> 00:23:23.460 align:middle line:84%
And I was just
like, I can't do it.

00:23:23.460 --> 00:23:26.790 align:middle line:84%
I just could not
see myself doing it.

00:23:26.790 --> 00:23:30.400 align:middle line:90%
So I didn't go, just no-show.

00:23:30.400 --> 00:23:32.850 align:middle line:84%
And then they badgered me
and called my house and left

00:23:32.850 --> 00:23:36.840 align:middle line:84%
messages on my answering machine
and sent me a certified letter.

00:23:36.840 --> 00:23:40.350 align:middle line:84%
They were really trying
to get me into treatment,

00:23:40.350 --> 00:23:46.940 align:middle line:84%
and eventually left me alone
so I could just be free.

00:23:46.940 --> 00:23:51.330 align:middle line:84%
And then once-- I
realized that every time I

00:23:51.330 --> 00:23:55.680 align:middle line:84%
would hear from them,
fear would enter my life.

00:23:55.680 --> 00:23:57.990 align:middle line:84%
And the farther away I got
from the cancer industry,

00:23:57.990 --> 00:24:01.520 align:middle line:84%
the more confident I got
and the less fear I had

00:24:01.520 --> 00:24:04.305 align:middle line:84%
and the more of an
adventure it became.

00:24:04.305 --> 00:24:05.970 align:middle line:84%
And to most cancer
patients, they

00:24:05.970 --> 00:24:09.450 align:middle line:84%
don't look at it as
an adventure at all.

00:24:09.450 --> 00:24:15.210 align:middle line:84%
They look at the cancer
experience as just suffering.

00:24:15.210 --> 00:24:22.710 align:middle line:84%
It's just adversity and
obstacles and just struggle.

00:24:22.710 --> 00:24:26.160 align:middle line:84%
But because I made
this different choice,

00:24:26.160 --> 00:24:29.640 align:middle line:84%
yeah it was an adversity and
there was some mental struggle.

00:24:29.640 --> 00:24:35.100 align:middle line:84%
But physically, I didn't suffer
like a chemo patient suffers.

00:24:35.100 --> 00:24:37.550 align:middle line:84%
I was feeling really good
from raw food diet and juicing

00:24:37.550 --> 00:24:38.910 align:middle line:90%
and all the stuff I was doing.

00:24:38.910 --> 00:24:42.360 align:middle line:84%
And I was trying to rebuild my
body instead of tear it down.

00:24:42.360 --> 00:24:46.200 align:middle line:84%
I was trying to support
my body's ability

00:24:46.200 --> 00:24:49.622 align:middle line:90%
to heal and not hurt it.

00:24:49.622 --> 00:24:51.330 align:middle line:84%
Your immune system is
critical to health.

00:24:51.330 --> 00:24:53.790 align:middle line:84%
And if you destroy
your immune system,

00:24:53.790 --> 00:24:55.000 align:middle line:90%
you're just a sitting duck.

00:24:55.000 --> 00:24:57.165 align:middle line:84%
And chemo destroys
your immune system.

00:24:57.165 --> 00:24:59.290 align:middle line:84%
As I started to read and
research more about chemo,

00:24:59.290 --> 00:25:03.420 align:middle line:84%
I was like, oh, man, it's
worse than I thought.

00:25:03.420 --> 00:25:08.240 align:middle line:84%
And so I just started to look at
it like, this is an adventure.

00:25:08.240 --> 00:25:10.850 align:middle line:90%
I need to enjoy the process.

00:25:10.850 --> 00:25:12.610 align:middle line:90%
I don't know what's coming next.

00:25:12.610 --> 00:25:14.520 align:middle line:90%
I just need to enjoy every day.

00:25:14.520 --> 00:25:18.150 align:middle line:84%
And every time fear
would creep in,

00:25:18.150 --> 00:25:21.750 align:middle line:84%
I would have to
immediately catch it,

00:25:21.750 --> 00:25:23.880 align:middle line:84%
catch myself in
those fear moments.

00:25:23.880 --> 00:25:26.740 align:middle line:84%
Because with cancer, every
single day, you're wondering,

00:25:26.740 --> 00:25:30.210 align:middle line:84%
am I getting better or
worse, every day you wake up.

00:25:30.210 --> 00:25:32.300 align:middle line:84%
It's like the opposite
of a nightmare.

00:25:32.300 --> 00:25:34.365 align:middle line:84%
You know when you
have a nightmare and--

00:25:34.365 --> 00:25:36.240 align:middle line:84%
have you ever had a
nightmare where maybe you

00:25:36.240 --> 00:25:39.165 align:middle line:84%
lost your wallet or
something important to you

00:25:39.165 --> 00:25:40.540 align:middle line:84%
and then you wake
up you're like,

00:25:40.540 --> 00:25:45.090 align:middle line:84%
oh, oh, it was just
a dream, I still

00:25:45.090 --> 00:25:48.480 align:middle line:84%
have my wallet, or
whatever, or something?

00:25:48.480 --> 00:25:49.750 align:middle line:90%
Cancer's the opposite.

00:25:49.750 --> 00:25:50.550 align:middle line:90%
You're asleep.

00:25:50.550 --> 00:25:51.060 align:middle line:90%
You're dreaming.

00:25:51.060 --> 00:25:51.660 align:middle line:90%
Everything's good.

00:25:51.660 --> 00:25:53.785 align:middle line:84%
You're waking up and you're
feeling good and happy.

00:25:53.785 --> 00:25:55.740 align:middle line:84%
And then you remember
you have cancer.

00:25:55.740 --> 00:25:58.560 align:middle line:90%
And then the nightmare starts.

00:25:58.560 --> 00:26:00.840 align:middle line:84%
It's that nightmare
feeling every morning

00:26:00.840 --> 00:26:06.870 align:middle line:84%
when you wake up to your reality
that is basically a nightmare.

00:26:06.870 --> 00:26:10.650 align:middle line:84%
And so every day, you have
this struggle with fear.

00:26:10.650 --> 00:26:11.490 align:middle line:90%
Is it coming back?

00:26:11.490 --> 00:26:12.720 align:middle line:90%
Am I getting better or worse?

00:26:12.720 --> 00:26:14.280 align:middle line:90%
What's happening?

00:26:14.280 --> 00:26:16.740 align:middle line:90%
Am I going to live?

00:26:16.740 --> 00:26:18.840 align:middle line:90%
How much time do I have left?

00:26:18.840 --> 00:26:21.450 align:middle line:84%
What do I need to be doing
right now with my life, all

00:26:21.450 --> 00:26:22.500 align:middle line:90%
these questions.

00:26:22.500 --> 00:26:24.570 align:middle line:90%
And nobody's asking themselves.

00:26:24.570 --> 00:26:27.075 align:middle line:84%
They're just going about
their little, happy lives,

00:26:27.075 --> 00:26:30.210 align:middle line:84%
punching the clock and driving
their little car around

00:26:30.210 --> 00:26:31.740 align:middle line:84%
and having fun
with their friends

00:26:31.740 --> 00:26:34.250 align:middle line:84%
and having drinks like
everybody else in the world.

00:26:34.250 --> 00:26:36.502 align:middle line:90%
And I'm so jealous of them.

00:26:36.502 --> 00:26:38.460 align:middle line:84%
Because everybody's just
so happy and oblivious

00:26:38.460 --> 00:26:43.460 align:middle line:84%
and I'm struggling
with this every day.

00:26:43.460 --> 00:26:45.510 align:middle line:84%
But I realized that
I had to get control

00:26:45.510 --> 00:26:48.270 align:middle line:84%
of my thoughts and my
emotions, that I couldn't

00:26:48.270 --> 00:26:52.260 align:middle line:84%
let my emotions rule me and I
couldn't let fear take over.

00:26:52.260 --> 00:26:54.960 align:middle line:84%
And so as fear would creep
in, I would just catch it.

00:26:54.960 --> 00:26:58.680 align:middle line:84%
I would catch myself in
the feeling, in the fear,

00:26:58.680 --> 00:27:01.090 align:middle line:90%
and give it to God.

00:27:01.090 --> 00:27:04.980 align:middle line:84%
I would just be like,
OK, you're in control.

00:27:04.980 --> 00:27:06.570 align:middle line:90%
I trust you.

00:27:06.570 --> 00:27:08.160 align:middle line:90%
I'm just giving you my fear.

00:27:08.160 --> 00:27:09.450 align:middle line:90%
I'm letting it go.

00:27:09.450 --> 00:27:11.470 align:middle line:90%
I'm not going to be afraid.

00:27:11.470 --> 00:27:13.230 align:middle line:90%
So I was choosing.

00:27:13.230 --> 00:27:15.660 align:middle line:90%
I was making this mental choice.

00:27:15.660 --> 00:27:18.390 align:middle line:84%
Because there is a difference
between your thoughts

00:27:18.390 --> 00:27:19.980 align:middle line:90%
and your emotions.

00:27:19.980 --> 00:27:23.490 align:middle line:84%
And your thoughts can
influence your emotions.

00:27:23.490 --> 00:27:25.920 align:middle line:84%
But a lot of times, we just
let our emotions influence

00:27:25.920 --> 00:27:29.410 align:middle line:84%
our thoughts, but
they don't have to.

00:27:29.410 --> 00:27:31.980 align:middle line:90%
So I had to train myself--

00:27:31.980 --> 00:27:34.020 align:middle line:84%
and these are not
things I just made up,

00:27:34.020 --> 00:27:36.360 align:middle line:84%
just reading other
people that had healed,

00:27:36.360 --> 00:27:38.400 align:middle line:90%
healers and survivors and--

00:27:38.400 --> 00:27:42.300 align:middle line:84%
I was just learning about how
powerful our thoughts are.

00:27:42.300 --> 00:27:44.700 align:middle line:84%
And I had learned things
from success authors

00:27:44.700 --> 00:27:45.720 align:middle line:90%
and being in sales.

00:27:45.720 --> 00:27:48.990 align:middle line:84%
So some of these concepts
were already there.

00:27:48.990 --> 00:27:54.990 align:middle line:84%
And so I just realized I had to
catch these fearful thoughts,

00:27:54.990 --> 00:27:58.290 align:middle line:84%
give them to God, and make
a choice not to be afraid

00:27:58.290 --> 00:28:01.350 align:middle line:84%
and not to worry, not to worry
about the things you can't

00:28:01.350 --> 00:28:04.440 align:middle line:84%
control, like, I'm just going
to focus on what I can control.

00:28:04.440 --> 00:28:05.610 align:middle line:90%
I can take care of myself.

00:28:05.610 --> 00:28:07.890 align:middle line:84%
I can eat this
hardcore raw food, tons

00:28:07.890 --> 00:28:10.947 align:middle line:84%
of fruits and vegetables diet,
15 to 20 servings of fruits

00:28:10.947 --> 00:28:12.030 align:middle line:90%
and vegetables every day--

00:28:12.030 --> 00:28:15.510 align:middle line:90%
it was hardcore-- plus juicing.

00:28:15.510 --> 00:28:19.500 align:middle line:90%
And that much I can do.

00:28:19.500 --> 00:28:22.360 align:middle line:84%
And I can do supplements and
I can do some other therapies.

00:28:22.360 --> 00:28:23.160 align:middle line:90%
That much I can do.

00:28:23.160 --> 00:28:24.953 align:middle line:84%
The rest, I just
can't worry about.

00:28:24.953 --> 00:28:26.370 align:middle line:84%
I just can't worry
about tomorrow.

00:28:26.370 --> 00:28:29.180 align:middle line:90%
I have to enjoy today, now.

00:28:29.180 --> 00:28:34.200 align:middle line:84%
And once I started to think
that way and retrain my brain,

00:28:34.200 --> 00:28:39.030 align:middle line:84%
I started practicing
gratitude, I found this--

00:28:39.030 --> 00:28:41.940 align:middle line:90%
it was like this--

00:28:41.940 --> 00:28:47.240 align:middle line:84%
it was like an
undiscovered level of bliss

00:28:47.240 --> 00:28:49.620 align:middle line:90%
that I could switch on.

00:28:49.620 --> 00:28:52.620 align:middle line:84%
And it was like-- man,
it was like a drug.

00:28:52.620 --> 00:28:54.900 align:middle line:84%
It was like the high on
life, like, I'm high on life.

00:28:54.900 --> 00:28:57.180 align:middle line:84%
That, to me, I always
thought was dumb.

00:28:57.180 --> 00:28:59.040 align:middle line:84%
And then all the sudden,
I was feeling it.

00:28:59.040 --> 00:29:01.770 align:middle line:84%
I was feeling the
high on life feeling.

00:29:01.770 --> 00:29:03.240 align:middle line:84%
And it wasn't all
day, every day.

00:29:03.240 --> 00:29:08.730 align:middle line:84%
But I would get these surges of
just having so much gratitude

00:29:08.730 --> 00:29:12.510 align:middle line:84%
just to be able to get in
my car and go to the store

00:29:12.510 --> 00:29:16.455 align:middle line:84%
and get some stuff,
just to be on my feet.

00:29:16.455 --> 00:29:18.330 align:middle line:84%
I'd been laid up and
recovering from surgery.

00:29:18.330 --> 00:29:20.940 align:middle line:84%
So that reset my
perspective on just like,

00:29:20.940 --> 00:29:24.810 align:middle line:84%
oh, it sure is nice to be
able to jog again or walk

00:29:24.810 --> 00:29:26.920 align:middle line:84%
because I couldn't do
that for a little while.

00:29:26.920 --> 00:29:31.410 align:middle line:84%
And so yeah, I had this
really intense bliss

00:29:31.410 --> 00:29:36.630 align:middle line:84%
that I was cultivating
through gratitude and then

00:29:36.630 --> 00:29:39.510 align:middle line:84%
through taking every
thought captive, which

00:29:39.510 --> 00:29:43.260 align:middle line:84%
is a biblical concept,
controlling your thoughts

00:29:43.260 --> 00:29:46.140 align:middle line:84%
and catching yourself when
you're being judgmental

00:29:46.140 --> 00:29:50.310 align:middle line:84%
or being envious or
criticizing others,

00:29:50.310 --> 00:29:54.960 align:middle line:84%
criticizing yourself, letting
bitterness and resentment

00:29:54.960 --> 00:29:57.660 align:middle line:84%
fester toward people
that have hurt you

00:29:57.660 --> 00:29:59.070 align:middle line:90%
and wronged you in some way.

00:29:59.070 --> 00:30:03.240 align:middle line:90%


00:30:03.240 --> 00:30:07.630 align:middle line:84%
I realized I had a lot
of negative thoughts.

00:30:07.630 --> 00:30:10.170 align:middle line:90%
I was just a negative person.

00:30:10.170 --> 00:30:11.670 align:middle line:84%
I just realized,
man, I'm a mess.

00:30:11.670 --> 00:30:14.310 align:middle line:90%
I'm a mental/emotional mess.

00:30:14.310 --> 00:30:16.050 align:middle line:90%
I don't know how I got this way.

00:30:16.050 --> 00:30:18.660 align:middle line:84%
But over time, I just
became more and more

00:30:18.660 --> 00:30:22.530 align:middle line:84%
insecure, at the same time,
prideful and judgmental and

00:30:22.530 --> 00:30:26.780 align:middle line:84%
critical and just
awful on the inside.

00:30:26.780 --> 00:30:29.180 align:middle line:84%
Although I was trying
to be a good person,

00:30:29.180 --> 00:30:33.650 align:middle line:84%
I was just awful not
to people physically,

00:30:33.650 --> 00:30:37.160 align:middle line:84%
but just all these swirling
negativity and stuff.

00:30:37.160 --> 00:30:40.990 align:middle line:84%
And so I was looking in
the mirror and saying,

00:30:40.990 --> 00:30:45.890 align:middle line:84%
OK, I have to deal
with this stuff.

00:30:45.890 --> 00:30:47.560 align:middle line:84%
I can't continue
living this way.

00:30:47.560 --> 00:30:50.540 align:middle line:84%
Maybe this is why
I'm sick, because I

00:30:50.540 --> 00:30:54.320 align:middle line:84%
have so much negativity
swirling around in my mind

00:30:54.320 --> 00:30:58.430 align:middle line:84%
and that's translating into my
body and it's suppressing me

00:30:58.430 --> 00:30:59.540 align:middle line:90%
and it's making me sick.

00:30:59.540 --> 00:31:03.350 align:middle line:84%
Well, later, I learn that
those same stress hormones

00:31:03.350 --> 00:31:05.420 align:middle line:84%
that happen when you're
in fight or flight

00:31:05.420 --> 00:31:09.380 align:middle line:84%
mode, adrenaline and cortisol,
when those stress hormones are

00:31:09.380 --> 00:31:14.300 align:middle line:84%
pumping, they suppress
your immune system

00:31:14.300 --> 00:31:16.830 align:middle line:90%
and they promote inflammation.

00:31:16.830 --> 00:31:19.953 align:middle line:84%
And so a lot of people,
many, many people--

00:31:19.953 --> 00:31:22.370 align:middle line:84%
I've talked to hundreds of
cancer patients over the years.

00:31:22.370 --> 00:31:23.945 align:middle line:84%
Every single one
of them tells you--

00:31:23.945 --> 00:31:25.820 align:middle line:84%
if you ask, why do you
think you have cancer,

00:31:25.820 --> 00:31:27.470 align:middle line:90%
they always say stress.

00:31:27.470 --> 00:31:31.673 align:middle line:84%
They know that stress was a
big part of their problem.

00:31:31.673 --> 00:31:33.090 align:middle line:84%
But when you have
all this stress,

00:31:33.090 --> 00:31:35.540 align:middle line:84%
whether it's unforgiveness
or bitterness or relationship

00:31:35.540 --> 00:31:38.270 align:middle line:84%
problems or negative
thinking and envy, jealousy,

00:31:38.270 --> 00:31:40.790 align:middle line:84%
all this stuff,
you are in a state

00:31:40.790 --> 00:31:43.790 align:middle line:84%
of chronic low-level
stress, which

00:31:43.790 --> 00:31:46.250 align:middle line:84%
is a state of chronic
immunosuppression

00:31:46.250 --> 00:31:49.470 align:middle line:90%
and inflammation.

00:31:49.470 --> 00:31:52.010 align:middle line:84%
And I was like, man, this is
making so much sense to me.

00:31:52.010 --> 00:31:55.040 align:middle line:84%
I've got to change this
as fast as possible

00:31:55.040 --> 00:31:56.060 align:middle line:90%
if I want to get well.

00:31:56.060 --> 00:31:58.130 align:middle line:90%
And so I was willing to change.

00:31:58.130 --> 00:31:59.422 align:middle line:90%
That's really the bottom line.

00:31:59.422 --> 00:32:01.130 align:middle line:84%
I was willing to change
everything, break

00:32:01.130 --> 00:32:06.020 align:middle line:84%
all my bad habits and break
all my bad thought habits,

00:32:06.020 --> 00:32:08.390 align:middle line:90%
which are the hardest to break.

00:32:08.390 --> 00:32:12.800 align:middle line:84%
Physical habits aren't as hard
as your bad thinking patterns

00:32:12.800 --> 00:32:14.240 align:middle line:90%
and habits.

00:32:14.240 --> 00:32:16.310 align:middle line:84%
But if you break
those, it's very easy

00:32:16.310 --> 00:32:18.512 align:middle line:90%
to break the physical habits.

00:32:18.512 --> 00:32:24.410 align:middle line:90%
So I just got busy doing it.

00:32:24.410 --> 00:32:29.540 align:middle line:84%
To me, at that time,
it was life or death.

00:32:29.540 --> 00:32:32.810 align:middle line:84%
It wasn't like, oh, I
should probably eat better.

00:32:32.810 --> 00:32:38.120 align:middle line:84%
It's like, everybody I know
knows I'm not doing chemo

00:32:38.120 --> 00:32:40.460 align:middle line:90%
and thinks I'm crazy.

00:32:40.460 --> 00:32:43.610 align:middle line:90%
And I don't want to die a fool.

00:32:43.610 --> 00:32:46.580 align:middle line:84%
So I better be willing
to pull out all the stops

00:32:46.580 --> 00:32:49.100 align:middle line:90%
and just go hardcore.

00:32:49.100 --> 00:32:52.010 align:middle line:84%
I'm kidding myself
if I think I'm just

00:32:52.010 --> 00:32:56.200 align:middle line:84%
going to take a few herbs or
something and cure my cancer.

00:32:56.200 --> 00:32:59.840 align:middle line:84%
So I've got to do
everything I can possibly

00:32:59.840 --> 00:33:05.330 align:middle line:84%
do at the most extreme
level that I can handle.

00:33:05.330 --> 00:33:07.550 align:middle line:84%
Heroic doses of
fruits and vegetables,

00:33:07.550 --> 00:33:11.530 align:middle line:84%
essentially, is
what I was doing.

00:33:11.530 --> 00:33:13.730 align:middle line:84%
And as I analyzed and
read and researched,

00:33:13.730 --> 00:33:20.000 align:middle line:84%
I just thought, well, it ain't
chemo, so I'll take as much

00:33:20.000 --> 00:33:22.860 align:middle line:84%
of it as I can stand,
whether it's garlic or ginger

00:33:22.860 --> 00:33:26.740 align:middle line:90%
or cayenne pepper or whatever.

00:33:26.740 --> 00:33:31.850 align:middle line:84%
So that was the adventure part
happening at the same time me,

00:33:31.850 --> 00:33:36.590 align:middle line:84%
having an adventure mindset and
trying to focus on gratitude.

00:33:36.590 --> 00:33:39.740 align:middle line:84%
Because gratitude is
the secret to happiness.

00:33:39.740 --> 00:33:42.200 align:middle line:90%
It really is the secret.

00:33:42.200 --> 00:33:45.350 align:middle line:84%
The secret to
unhappiness is when

00:33:45.350 --> 00:33:48.505 align:middle line:84%
you focus on the
things you don't have,

00:33:48.505 --> 00:33:49.880 align:middle line:84%
the things that
you wish you had,

00:33:49.880 --> 00:33:51.890 align:middle line:84%
the things that
other people have.

00:33:51.890 --> 00:33:55.460 align:middle line:84%
When you focus on people
that have more than you,

00:33:55.460 --> 00:34:02.070 align:middle line:84%
it fosters envy and
jealousy and unhappiness.

00:34:02.070 --> 00:34:05.330 align:middle line:84%
But when you focus on people
that have less than you,

00:34:05.330 --> 00:34:08.420 align:middle line:84%
it fosters gratitude
and thankfulness.

00:34:08.420 --> 00:34:10.870 align:middle line:84%
Because you realize,
wow, I'm so blessed.

00:34:10.870 --> 00:34:12.139 align:middle line:90%
I have so much.

00:34:12.139 --> 00:34:19.370 align:middle line:84%
I don't live in a tin
hut in the Philippines.

00:34:19.370 --> 00:34:22.730 align:middle line:84%
I'm so blessed to be born
in the United States,

00:34:22.730 --> 00:34:26.330 align:middle line:84%
in a Western nation
that has clean drinking

00:34:26.330 --> 00:34:30.110 align:middle line:84%
water and electricity
and food everywhere.

00:34:30.110 --> 00:34:33.260 align:middle line:84%
And I have a family that loves
me and a wife that loves me.

00:34:33.260 --> 00:34:35.372 align:middle line:84%
So when I start
counting my blessings--

00:34:35.372 --> 00:34:36.830 align:middle line:84%
and then all the
sudden, it's like,

00:34:36.830 --> 00:34:38.929 align:middle line:84%
wow, man, I don't
even know what I

00:34:38.929 --> 00:34:42.530 align:middle line:84%
was upset about a minute ago
because my life is really

00:34:42.530 --> 00:34:43.370 align:middle line:90%
so good.

00:34:43.370 --> 00:34:45.050 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, the cancer
thing is a challenge.

00:34:45.050 --> 00:34:49.139 align:middle line:84%
But I have so much to
be thankful for that all

00:34:49.139 --> 00:34:52.909 align:middle line:84%
the sudden, it just puts
it all in perspective.

00:34:52.909 --> 00:35:00.340 align:middle line:84%
And so gratitude plus
actively taking my thoughts

00:35:00.340 --> 00:35:03.140 align:middle line:84%
and being-- mindfulness
is what they call it now.

00:35:03.140 --> 00:35:05.780 align:middle line:84%
Back then, I'd never
heard that term.

00:35:05.780 --> 00:35:08.960 align:middle line:84%
But catching myself thinking
negatively and changing

00:35:08.960 --> 00:35:11.982 align:middle line:84%
the way I thought,
plus gratitude,

00:35:11.982 --> 00:35:13.190 align:middle line:90%
is the way I dealt with fear.

