00:35:16.613 --> 00:35:21.020 align:middle line:90%


00:35:21.020 --> 00:35:24.770 align:middle line:84%
I've thought a lot about
the stress connection

00:35:24.770 --> 00:35:31.010 align:middle line:84%
to cancer and the
mental-emotional-spiritual

00:35:31.010 --> 00:35:34.640 align:middle line:84%
connection to your
physical body.

00:35:34.640 --> 00:35:37.700 align:middle line:84%
And I can make a
pretty strong case

00:35:37.700 --> 00:35:44.210 align:middle line:84%
that stress is the root cause
of most chronic disease.

00:35:44.210 --> 00:35:45.500 align:middle line:90%
And this is why.

00:35:45.500 --> 00:35:48.740 align:middle line:84%
Because when you are
stressed, whether you're

00:35:48.740 --> 00:35:53.960 align:middle line:84%
in a state of chronic
worry and anxiety or fear

00:35:53.960 --> 00:35:58.310 align:middle line:84%
or resentment or bitterness or
unforgiveness, jealousy envy,

00:35:58.310 --> 00:36:01.580 align:middle line:84%
if you're entertaining
those emotions every day,

00:36:01.580 --> 00:36:04.010 align:middle line:84%
multiple, all of
them, some of them,

00:36:04.010 --> 00:36:09.350 align:middle line:84%
whatever, then you stay in
a state of chronic stress.

00:36:09.350 --> 00:36:12.050 align:middle line:84%
And chronic stress
promotes inflammation

00:36:12.050 --> 00:36:15.650 align:middle line:84%
and it suppresses your
immunity physiologically.

00:36:15.650 --> 00:36:23.950 align:middle line:84%
And so you create an environment
in which cancer can thrive.

00:36:23.950 --> 00:36:25.880 align:middle line:90%
And it doesn't happen overnight.

00:36:25.880 --> 00:36:27.500 align:middle line:84%
It's not like, oh I
got in a car wreck

00:36:27.500 --> 00:36:30.080 align:middle line:84%
and it was really stressful,
like, oh, no, I got cancer.

00:36:30.080 --> 00:36:31.250 align:middle line:90%
It's not like that.

00:36:31.250 --> 00:36:34.280 align:middle line:84%
It's people that are living in
this state of chronic stress

00:36:34.280 --> 00:36:40.070 align:middle line:84%
for years, usually, could
be even a decade of a really

00:36:40.070 --> 00:36:44.810 align:middle line:84%
difficult marriage, an abusive
relationship, an abusive work

00:36:44.810 --> 00:36:45.698 align:middle line:90%
environment.

00:36:45.698 --> 00:36:47.240 align:middle line:84%
They go through a
really bad lawsuit.

00:36:47.240 --> 00:36:48.580 align:middle line:90%
They lose their business.

00:36:48.580 --> 00:36:50.870 align:middle line:84%
They have a death in the
family or multiple deaths

00:36:50.870 --> 00:36:53.720 align:middle line:84%
in the family or
loved ones or friends.

00:36:53.720 --> 00:36:56.300 align:middle line:84%
And I hear these stories
over and over and over

00:36:56.300 --> 00:37:00.690 align:middle line:84%
from cancer patients when I
talk to them about their life.

00:37:00.690 --> 00:37:02.300 align:middle line:90%
I'm not a doctor.

00:37:02.300 --> 00:37:03.628 align:middle line:90%
I'm just a friend.

00:37:03.628 --> 00:37:05.420 align:middle line:84%
And so I get into
people's lives and I just

00:37:05.420 --> 00:37:07.253 align:middle line:84%
want to know, like,
tell me about your life.

00:37:07.253 --> 00:37:08.100 align:middle line:90%
What was going on?

00:37:08.100 --> 00:37:11.060 align:middle line:84%
And every time,
they always start

00:37:11.060 --> 00:37:13.550 align:middle line:84%
telling me, well, I had
this really, really, really

00:37:13.550 --> 00:37:14.360 align:middle line:90%
terrible job.

00:37:14.360 --> 00:37:17.840 align:middle line:84%
I changed jobs and it was really
awful or went through a divorce

00:37:17.840 --> 00:37:20.490 align:middle line:84%
or I lost my spouse,
lost my business.

00:37:20.490 --> 00:37:24.800 align:middle line:90%
So that leads them--

00:37:24.800 --> 00:37:25.640 align:middle line:90%
it's like this.

00:37:25.640 --> 00:37:30.140 align:middle line:84%
They're teetering on the
brink of disease for years.

00:37:30.140 --> 00:37:33.380 align:middle line:84%
And then oftentimes,
there's one traumatic event

00:37:33.380 --> 00:37:35.824 align:middle line:90%
that pushes them over the edge.

00:37:35.824 --> 00:37:38.870 align:middle line:84%
So they've got chronic
stress for years.

00:37:38.870 --> 00:37:45.650 align:middle line:84%
And then bam, someone important
to them dies or their career is

00:37:45.650 --> 00:37:50.210 align:middle line:84%
over for some reason or they
lose their home, bankruptcy.

00:37:50.210 --> 00:37:53.280 align:middle line:84%
And that's what we call the
stress trigger or the cancer

00:37:53.280 --> 00:37:54.080 align:middle line:90%
trigger.

00:37:54.080 --> 00:37:57.270 align:middle line:84%
It's just the straw that
broke the camel's back.

00:37:57.270 --> 00:37:59.690 align:middle line:84%
And then within a few
months or a year--

00:37:59.690 --> 00:38:02.480 align:middle line:84%
you can usually trace
it back just a few years

00:38:02.480 --> 00:38:05.827 align:middle line:84%
to a very traumatic
event in someone's life.

00:38:05.827 --> 00:38:07.910 align:middle line:84%
And then a few years later,
a year or two, they've

00:38:07.910 --> 00:38:10.610 align:middle line:90%
got a noticeable size tumor.

00:38:10.610 --> 00:38:13.260 align:middle line:90%
They find a tumor somewhere.

00:38:13.260 --> 00:38:17.720 align:middle line:84%
And so you can make this
case, and I do make the case,

00:38:17.720 --> 00:38:22.580 align:middle line:84%
that stress is the root cause
of almost all chronic disease.

00:38:22.580 --> 00:38:27.290 align:middle line:84%
Because prolonged stress keeps
us in a vulnerable state.

00:38:27.290 --> 00:38:30.570 align:middle line:84%
And if you're in a vulnerable,
weak state long enough,

00:38:30.570 --> 00:38:33.680 align:middle line:84%
your body becomes a place
where cancer can thrive.

00:38:33.680 --> 00:38:37.460 align:middle line:84%
If you've got a person
that's been in chronic stress

00:38:37.460 --> 00:38:43.100 align:middle line:84%
for years and they develop
cancer, well, guess what.

00:38:43.100 --> 00:38:50.150 align:middle line:84%
The cancer diagnosis itself is
a traumatic, stressful event.

00:38:50.150 --> 00:38:57.590 align:middle line:84%
And cancer patients can get
PTSD just from the diagnosis.

00:38:57.590 --> 00:38:58.850 align:middle line:90%
It's that stressful.

00:38:58.850 --> 00:38:59.900 align:middle line:90%
It's that traumatic.

00:38:59.900 --> 00:39:03.940 align:middle line:90%
It's that powerful.

00:39:03.940 --> 00:39:08.120 align:middle line:84%
They have symptoms
of PTSD because it's

00:39:08.120 --> 00:39:11.182 align:middle line:84%
such a scary just
bomb in their life.

00:39:11.182 --> 00:39:12.140 align:middle line:90%
And guess what happens.

00:39:12.140 --> 00:39:14.682 align:middle line:84%
Well, all that stress has been
contributing to their disease.

00:39:14.682 --> 00:39:16.530 align:middle line:90%
Now they get a stress bomb.

00:39:16.530 --> 00:39:20.600 align:middle line:84%
And their immune
system goes even lower

00:39:20.600 --> 00:39:22.880 align:middle line:90%
and they become even weaker.

00:39:22.880 --> 00:39:26.456 align:middle line:90%
And it's not uncommon to see--

00:39:26.456 --> 00:39:28.790 align:middle line:84%
doctors will often
tell a patient, well,

00:39:28.790 --> 00:39:30.660 align:middle line:84%
cancer grows very
slowly typically.

00:39:30.660 --> 00:39:31.490 align:middle line:84%
And this has
probably been growing

00:39:31.490 --> 00:39:33.860 align:middle line:84%
for many years in your body
and now, it's just finally

00:39:33.860 --> 00:39:35.540 align:middle line:90%
big enough for us to find it.

00:39:35.540 --> 00:39:37.250 align:middle line:84%
But then as soon as
they're diagnosed,

00:39:37.250 --> 00:39:43.160 align:middle line:84%
it starts growing very fast
and metastasizes quickly.

00:39:43.160 --> 00:39:44.000 align:middle line:90%
What happened?

00:39:44.000 --> 00:39:45.710 align:middle line:90%
It was growing slowly.

00:39:45.710 --> 00:39:47.510 align:middle line:84%
And now it's
growing really fast.

00:39:47.510 --> 00:39:51.590 align:middle line:84%
It's the traumatic stress
response in the body.

00:39:51.590 --> 00:39:54.590 align:middle line:84%
It's even more
immunosuppression, even more

00:39:54.590 --> 00:40:01.950 align:middle line:84%
worry and fear and anxiety
that is weakening them further.

00:40:01.950 --> 00:40:03.860 align:middle line:90%
And that's scary.

00:40:03.860 --> 00:40:05.860 align:middle line:84%
And it's something that
no one is talking about.

