We use electricity.

00:43:50.440 --> 00:43:52.430 align:middle line:84%
We stay up way later
than we should.

00:43:52.430 --> 00:43:54.430 align:middle line:84%
We're not getting as much
sleep as our ancestors

00:43:54.430 --> 00:43:55.930 align:middle line:90%
because we stay up late.

00:43:55.930 --> 00:43:57.387 align:middle line:90%
So even my sleep habits changed.

00:43:57.387 --> 00:43:58.970 align:middle line:84%
I realized, I need
to go to bed early.

00:43:58.970 --> 00:44:02.500 align:middle line:84%
I need to go to bed much closer
to when the sun goes down.

00:44:02.500 --> 00:44:06.780 align:middle line:84%
And the seasons obviously
change throughout the year

00:44:06.780 --> 00:44:08.530 align:middle line:84%
and the amount of
daylight we have changes

00:44:08.530 --> 00:44:09.590 align:middle line:90%
throughout the year.

00:44:09.590 --> 00:44:11.810 align:middle line:84%
And so parts of the year,
you have a lot of daylight

00:44:11.810 --> 00:44:13.000 align:middle line:84%
and you don't need
as much sleep.

00:44:13.000 --> 00:44:14.375 align:middle line:84%
But then other
parts of the year,

00:44:14.375 --> 00:44:16.930 align:middle line:84%
the winter, at
least in the US, you

00:44:16.930 --> 00:44:20.290 align:middle line:84%
have a lot less
daylight and more night.

00:44:20.290 --> 00:44:22.510 align:middle line:84%
Maybe we need more
sleep in the winter.

00:44:22.510 --> 00:44:24.010 align:middle line:84%
So I was thinking
about these things

00:44:24.010 --> 00:44:26.170 align:middle line:84%
and really made changes
in my life that way,

00:44:26.170 --> 00:44:32.200 align:middle line:84%
too, to, again, just try to
live in harmony with the earth,

00:44:32.200 --> 00:44:35.950 align:middle line:84%
with nature, eating
food from the earth,

00:44:35.950 --> 00:44:40.530 align:middle line:84%
just trying to
figure it all out.

00:44:40.530 --> 00:44:42.650 align:middle line:90%
And it all helped.

00:44:42.650 --> 00:44:43.450 align:middle line:90%
All of those--

00:44:43.450 --> 00:44:46.900 align:middle line:84%
We know now just from
science that lack of sleep

00:44:46.900 --> 00:44:49.030 align:middle line:84%
is a major stress
promoter in the body.

00:44:49.030 --> 00:44:53.650 align:middle line:84%
Lack of sleep, you end up
with elevated stress hormones,

00:44:53.650 --> 00:44:56.710 align:middle line:84%
adrenaline and cortisol, which
suppress your immune system

00:44:56.710 --> 00:44:58.270 align:middle line:90%
and promote inflammation.

00:44:58.270 --> 00:44:59.350 align:middle line:90%
Sleep is critical.

00:44:59.350 --> 00:45:01.840 align:middle line:90%
So we know that I'm getting--

00:45:01.840 --> 00:45:03.640 align:middle line:90%
a lot of people need--

00:45:03.640 --> 00:45:07.105 align:middle line:84%
it's just common-- you hear all
the time-- people say, oh, you

00:45:07.105 --> 00:45:08.980 align:middle line:84%
need six to eight hours
of sleep every night.

00:45:08.980 --> 00:45:11.860 align:middle line:84%
Some people need way
more than that, 8 to 10.

00:45:11.860 --> 00:45:15.040 align:middle line:84%
And I'm more in
the 8 to 10 range.

00:45:15.040 --> 00:45:16.250 align:middle line:90%
And it's fine.

00:45:16.250 --> 00:45:17.740 align:middle line:90%
I'm fine with it.

00:45:17.740 --> 00:45:19.490 align:middle line:84%
It's unfortunate that
we live in a culture

00:45:19.490 --> 00:45:22.100 align:middle line:84%
where people are so
obsessed with success

00:45:22.100 --> 00:45:25.140 align:middle line:90%
and achievement that they--

00:45:25.140 --> 00:45:30.140 align:middle line:84%
I'm constantly reading
articles about life hacking

00:45:30.140 --> 00:45:34.610 align:middle line:84%
or hacking the human body,
biohacking, where, how

00:45:34.610 --> 00:45:40.880 align:middle line:84%
can I function at peak
performance 23 hours a day

00:45:40.880 --> 00:45:43.640 align:middle line:84%
and only function
on 1 hour's sleep?

00:45:43.640 --> 00:45:45.980 align:middle line:84%
Maybe I need to drink
this special coffee

00:45:45.980 --> 00:45:47.930 align:middle line:90%
concoction and or whatever.

00:45:47.930 --> 00:45:50.870 align:middle line:84%
So I'm totally not
into that at all.

00:45:50.870 --> 00:45:52.550 align:middle line:84%
I don't want to
biohack anything.

00:45:52.550 --> 00:45:55.520 align:middle line:84%
I just want to live naturally
in tune with the earth

00:45:55.520 --> 00:45:57.550 align:middle line:90%
and be healthy.

00:45:57.550 --> 00:46:01.040 align:middle line:84%
And if I need 8 to 10
hours of sleep, so be it.

00:46:01.040 --> 00:46:03.950 align:middle line:84%
I also set limits on
my workday beyond that.

00:46:03.950 --> 00:46:09.650 align:middle line:84%
I realized being a
workaholic is not healthy.

00:46:09.650 --> 00:46:12.620 align:middle line:84%
And so I started really
cutting my workday down

00:46:12.620 --> 00:46:15.640 align:middle line:84%
and spending time with my
family and with my wife.

00:46:15.640 --> 00:46:17.390 align:middle line:84%
And guess what happens
when you spend time

00:46:17.390 --> 00:46:18.265 align:middle line:90%
with people you love.

00:46:18.265 --> 00:46:20.750 align:middle line:90%
Your stress goes down.

00:46:20.750 --> 00:46:26.190 align:middle line:84%
And so yeah, there's so much
we can do to reduce stress.

00:46:26.190 --> 00:46:28.910 align:middle line:84%
And when you start
identifying all of the things

00:46:28.910 --> 00:46:32.710 align:middle line:84%
that we're doing
in modern society

00:46:32.710 --> 00:46:34.460 align:middle line:84%
or just what our daily
routines look like,

00:46:34.460 --> 00:46:39.075 align:middle line:84%
so much of our daily
routine is stress-promoting.

00:46:39.075 --> 00:46:42.860 align:middle line:84%
But there's so many easy
changes you can make,

00:46:42.860 --> 00:46:45.710 align:middle line:84%
getting more sleep,
exercising, eating

00:46:45.710 --> 00:46:48.570 align:middle line:84%
a diet that's rich in fruits
and vegetables from the earth,

00:46:48.570 --> 00:46:51.050 align:middle line:84%
plant-based diet, not
eating much meat and dairy

00:46:51.050 --> 00:46:54.080 align:middle line:84%
and processed food
and junk food,

00:46:54.080 --> 00:46:57.920 align:middle line:84%
spending time with your loved
ones, breathing fresh air,

00:46:57.920 --> 00:47:00.350 align:middle line:84%
getting sunshine,
connecting with the earth.

00:47:00.350 --> 00:47:02.090 align:middle line:90%
All these things are not hard.

00:47:02.090 --> 00:47:04.640 align:middle line:84%
Most of them don't
cost anything.

00:47:04.640 --> 00:47:10.580 align:middle line:84%
And they have such a deeply
profound and measurable effect

00:47:10.580 --> 00:47:12.890 align:middle line:84%
on the human body
and on our stress.

00:47:12.890 --> 00:47:18.150 align:middle line:84%
So it was just like I was on
an adventure, this healing

00:47:18.150 --> 00:47:18.950 align:middle line:90%
adventure.

00:47:18.950 --> 00:47:22.670 align:middle line:84%
And it was a systematic
process of discovery,

00:47:22.670 --> 00:47:24.980 align:middle line:84%
of trying to figure
out, what all can

00:47:24.980 --> 00:47:29.990 align:middle line:84%
I possibly change to help
me get well and stay well

00:47:29.990 --> 00:47:35.368 align:middle line:84%
and to help my immune system
deal with the existing cancer

00:47:35.368 --> 00:47:37.160 align:middle line:84%
cells that are circulating
in my body, that

00:47:37.160 --> 00:47:40.640 align:middle line:84%
are looking for a new place
to set up camp and start

00:47:40.640 --> 00:47:42.240 align:middle line:90%
reproducing?

00:47:42.240 --> 00:47:46.440 align:middle line:90%
And I did it.

00:47:46.440 --> 00:47:47.240 align:middle line:90%
I did it.

00:47:47.240 --> 00:47:49.500 align:middle line:90%
I just changed up my whole life.

00:47:49.500 --> 00:47:52.700 align:middle line:84%
I did everything I could find
and afford, made no excuses,

00:47:52.700 --> 00:47:54.740 align:middle line:84%
took full responsibility
for my health,

00:47:54.740 --> 00:47:56.615 align:middle line:84%
and trusted God to
lead me in the process.

