And the first
questions that I always

00:55:03.730 --> 00:55:08.110 align:middle line:84%
ask them to try to help them
understand their situation

00:55:08.110 --> 00:55:10.840 align:middle line:84%
and get clarity on
their life and for me

00:55:10.840 --> 00:55:17.230 align:middle line:84%
to understand what they're going
through and where they are is--

00:55:17.230 --> 00:55:24.380 align:middle line:84%
the first question is, why
do you think you have cancer?

00:55:24.380 --> 00:55:28.240 align:middle line:84%
And one of the answers
to that is always stress.

00:55:28.240 --> 00:55:33.760 align:middle line:84%
The second question is, do
you really want to live?

00:55:33.760 --> 00:55:37.840 align:middle line:90%
And it's interesting.

00:55:37.840 --> 00:55:42.610 align:middle line:84%
Some cancer patients, a small
percentage, it might be 10%,

00:55:42.610 --> 00:55:44.320 align:middle line:90%
don't want to live.

00:55:44.320 --> 00:55:45.220 align:middle line:90%
They're ready to die.

00:55:45.220 --> 00:55:46.660 align:middle line:90%
And it's OK.

00:55:46.660 --> 00:55:49.918 align:middle line:84%
Maybe they've had a long
life and they're older

00:55:49.918 --> 00:55:51.460 align:middle line:84%
and they're satisfied
with their life

00:55:51.460 --> 00:55:53.470 align:middle line:90%
and they're just OK with it.

00:55:53.470 --> 00:55:56.293 align:middle line:84%
There was a very
famous woman that--

00:55:56.293 --> 00:55:57.460 align:middle line:90%
I believe her name is Norma.

00:55:57.460 --> 00:55:58.330 align:middle line:90%
And she was in her 90s.

00:55:58.330 --> 00:55:59.890 align:middle line:84%
She got a terminal
cancer diagnosis.

00:55:59.890 --> 00:56:02.710 align:middle line:84%
And she refused all treatment
and went on this big road trip

00:56:02.710 --> 00:56:04.090 align:middle line:90%
around the US.

00:56:04.090 --> 00:56:06.100 align:middle line:84%
And it was-- "Driving
Miss Norma," I think,

00:56:06.100 --> 00:56:07.930 align:middle line:90%
was the Facebook page.

00:56:07.930 --> 00:56:10.540 align:middle line:84%
And they made this
Facebook page,

00:56:10.540 --> 00:56:13.810 align:middle line:84%
and posting pictures of her at
the Grand Canyon and skydiving,

00:56:13.810 --> 00:56:16.590 align:middle line:84%
all kinds of stuff, just having
all these adventures as she's

00:56:16.590 --> 00:56:18.460 align:middle line:90%
93 years old, I think--

00:56:18.460 --> 00:56:21.840 align:middle line:90%
maybe 91, but whatever--

00:56:21.840 --> 00:56:23.152 align:middle line:90%
and made this choice.

00:56:23.152 --> 00:56:24.610 align:middle line:84%
She was ready to
die and she wanted

00:56:24.610 --> 00:56:25.860 align:middle line:90%
to enjoy the rest of her life.

00:56:25.860 --> 00:56:27.640 align:middle line:90%
And it was fine.

00:56:27.640 --> 00:56:31.660 align:middle line:84%
Some cancer patients are
ready to die because they've

00:56:31.660 --> 00:56:35.770 align:middle line:84%
had a very difficult life
and cancer is a way out

00:56:35.770 --> 00:56:37.660 align:middle line:90%
if you just had a hard life.

00:56:37.660 --> 00:56:41.140 align:middle line:84%
And they're really deeply
depressed and discouraged

00:56:41.140 --> 00:56:43.310 align:middle line:90%
and unhappy.

00:56:43.310 --> 00:56:45.610 align:middle line:90%
And again, it's OK.

00:56:45.610 --> 00:56:48.500 align:middle line:84%
So you got maybe 10%
of cancer patients,

00:56:48.500 --> 00:56:50.370 align:middle line:84%
this is just my
rough estimation,

00:56:50.370 --> 00:56:51.970 align:middle line:90%
that are ready to die.

00:56:51.970 --> 00:56:56.530 align:middle line:84%
And then you've got the
rest that want to live.

00:56:56.530 --> 00:56:59.500 align:middle line:90%


00:56:59.500 --> 00:57:02.320 align:middle line:84%
Most of them, even if
they're ready to die,

00:57:02.320 --> 00:57:04.570 align:middle line:84%
it's very few of them that
will admit they are but you

00:57:04.570 --> 00:57:06.740 align:middle line:90%
can tell by their actions.

00:57:06.740 --> 00:57:13.510 align:middle line:84%
But the ones that want to
live, I have to ask them why.

00:57:13.510 --> 00:57:16.120 align:middle line:90%
So do you want to live?

00:57:16.120 --> 00:57:17.650 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:57:17.650 --> 00:57:18.700 align:middle line:90%
Why?

00:57:18.700 --> 00:57:21.210 align:middle line:90%
What do you have to live for?

00:57:21.210 --> 00:57:23.580 align:middle line:84%
And so I make them
think about it.

00:57:23.580 --> 00:57:25.960 align:middle line:84%
I want them to think
about what they have

00:57:25.960 --> 00:57:29.910 align:middle line:90%
to live for and figure it out.

00:57:29.910 --> 00:57:36.170 align:middle line:84%
And oh, well, I have two
kids that are in high school

00:57:36.170 --> 00:57:38.710 align:middle line:84%
or I want to see my
grandkids graduate

00:57:38.710 --> 00:57:42.910 align:middle line:90%
from college or whatever.

00:57:42.910 --> 00:57:49.570 align:middle line:84%
And so having that strong
not only will to live,

00:57:49.570 --> 00:57:54.130 align:middle line:84%
but something to live
for is really important.

00:57:54.130 --> 00:57:58.060 align:middle line:84%
And that's why you see with
older people, even sometimes

00:57:58.060 --> 00:58:01.960 align:middle line:84%
just middle age and
older, is they run out

00:58:01.960 --> 00:58:03.800 align:middle line:90%
of things to live for.

00:58:03.800 --> 00:58:06.850 align:middle line:90%
They've raised their kids.

00:58:06.850 --> 00:58:09.280 align:middle line:84%
Maybe they're not really in
touch with their grandkids

00:58:09.280 --> 00:58:11.440 align:middle line:84%
and maybe they're not
that close to them.

00:58:11.440 --> 00:58:14.440 align:middle line:84%
And maybe they're retired
or close to retirement.

00:58:14.440 --> 00:58:17.780 align:middle line:84%
And they feel like they've
lost their life's purpose.

00:58:17.780 --> 00:58:21.010 align:middle line:84%
They're just
drifting through life

00:58:21.010 --> 00:58:25.090 align:middle line:84%
not really making a
difference in the world

00:58:25.090 --> 00:58:29.050 align:middle line:90%
or in anyone's life around them.

00:58:29.050 --> 00:58:31.930 align:middle line:84%
And yeah, they just
don't have a will

00:58:31.930 --> 00:58:35.390 align:middle line:84%
to live because they
lost their purpose,

00:58:35.390 --> 00:58:37.540 align:middle line:90%
or maybe never found it.

00:58:37.540 --> 00:58:40.660 align:middle line:84%
And so what I try to do
is help people find that,

00:58:40.660 --> 00:58:43.110 align:middle line:84%
help them figure out what
they have to live for.

00:58:43.110 --> 00:58:47.390 align:middle line:90%
And once you do--

00:58:47.390 --> 00:58:49.880 align:middle line:90%
like for me, I had three--

00:58:49.880 --> 00:58:53.500 align:middle line:84%
well, in the beginning, I had
two major motivators for me.

00:58:53.500 --> 00:58:57.340 align:middle line:84%
The first was the thought
of my wife burying me.

00:58:57.340 --> 00:59:01.570 align:middle line:84%
We've been together for
eight years, married for two.

00:59:01.570 --> 00:59:04.840 align:middle line:84%
And I just couldn't
bear the thought of it.

00:59:04.840 --> 00:59:08.770 align:middle line:84%
And then equally
as hard to bear was

00:59:08.770 --> 00:59:12.055 align:middle line:84%
the thought of my parents
burying their only child.

00:59:12.055 --> 00:59:15.010 align:middle line:90%


00:59:15.010 --> 00:59:20.080 align:middle line:84%
That was such a painful thought,
just to even just put myself

00:59:20.080 --> 00:59:23.322 align:middle line:84%
in their shoes or empathize
or whatever and just

00:59:23.322 --> 00:59:25.030 align:middle line:84%
think about what it'd
be like to bury me.

00:59:25.030 --> 00:59:28.160 align:middle line:84%
Not that I'm super special,
but I mean a lot to them.

00:59:28.160 --> 00:59:30.380 align:middle line:90%
I'm their whole world.

00:59:30.380 --> 00:59:31.610 align:middle line:90%
I'm their whole world.

00:59:31.610 --> 00:59:32.410 align:middle line:90%
They're my parents.

00:59:32.410 --> 00:59:33.970 align:middle line:90%
I'm their only kid.

00:59:33.970 --> 00:59:37.690 align:middle line:84%
And I'm pretty much
my wife's whole world.

00:59:37.690 --> 00:59:40.660 align:middle line:84%
And so right in the
beginning, those

00:59:40.660 --> 00:59:42.940 align:middle line:90%
are my two strong motivators.

00:59:42.940 --> 00:59:47.530 align:middle line:84%
The third, to a
lesser degree, was

00:59:47.530 --> 00:59:49.150 align:middle line:90%
I wanted to experience life.

00:59:49.150 --> 00:59:51.970 align:middle line:90%
I wanted to have successes.

00:59:51.970 --> 00:59:55.500 align:middle line:90%
I wanted to have kids.

00:59:55.500 --> 00:59:56.860 align:middle line:90%
I was 26.

00:59:56.860 --> 00:59:58.590 align:middle line:90%
I still felt like a teenager.

00:59:58.590 --> 01:00:01.600 align:middle line:84%
I'm like, I'm just
getting started here.

01:00:01.600 --> 01:00:04.510 align:middle line:84%
I want more out
of life than what

01:00:04.510 --> 01:00:06.060 align:middle line:84%
I've gotten so
far, which is like,

01:00:06.060 --> 01:00:07.930 align:middle line:90%
I've barely made any money.

01:00:07.930 --> 01:00:12.360 align:middle line:84%
I barely got to do anything
really cool or fun.

01:00:12.360 --> 01:00:14.560 align:middle line:84%
Obviously, I had made some
good memories, of course,

01:00:14.560 --> 01:00:16.020 align:middle line:90%
like anybody in their 20s.

01:00:16.020 --> 01:00:18.910 align:middle line:84%
But yeah, I felt
like, wow, there's

01:00:18.910 --> 01:00:20.710 align:middle line:84%
so much I want to
do with my life

01:00:20.710 --> 01:00:23.200 align:middle line:84%
and figure out and learn
and explore and whatever.

01:00:23.200 --> 01:00:25.930 align:middle line:90%


01:00:25.930 --> 01:00:28.225 align:middle line:84%
But I was also afraid to
make plans for the future.

01:00:28.225 --> 01:00:31.090 align:middle line:90%


01:00:31.090 --> 01:00:35.500 align:middle line:84%
I was afraid to because I don't
know if I was going to die

01:00:35.500 --> 01:00:36.810 align:middle line:90%
or not.

01:00:36.810 --> 01:00:41.740 align:middle line:84%
And so that fear
of, I don't know;

01:00:41.740 --> 01:00:45.880 align:middle line:84%
I don't want to think too
far ahead because what if I

01:00:45.880 --> 01:00:48.220 align:middle line:90%
can't get there--

01:00:48.220 --> 01:00:51.340 align:middle line:84%
but I realized that making
plans for the future

01:00:51.340 --> 01:00:55.630 align:middle line:84%
was one of the best things I
could do because it got me out

01:00:55.630 --> 01:00:56.590 align:middle line:90%
of now.

01:00:56.590 --> 01:00:58.870 align:middle line:84%
It got me out of my
present problems.

01:00:58.870 --> 01:01:03.190 align:middle line:84%
And it got me thinking
through them and past them.

01:01:03.190 --> 01:01:05.260 align:middle line:84%
And it got me in
this I don't know,

01:01:05.260 --> 01:01:07.820 align:middle line:90%
success mindset or something.

01:01:07.820 --> 01:01:10.070 align:middle line:84%
Someone else could probably
explain it better than me.

01:01:10.070 --> 01:01:13.210 align:middle line:84%
But once my wife and
I decided to have kids

01:01:13.210 --> 01:01:16.810 align:middle line:84%
and she got pregnant, then it's
like, OK, now I have a future.

01:01:16.810 --> 01:01:19.900 align:middle line:84%
Now I have another thing
on my reasons to live

01:01:19.900 --> 01:01:23.160 align:middle line:90%
and things I need to live for.

01:01:23.160 --> 01:01:27.580 align:middle line:84%
And so we can
actually create things

01:01:27.580 --> 01:01:30.430 align:middle line:84%
to live for when
previously, we had none.

01:01:30.430 --> 01:01:34.900 align:middle line:84%
So if you're looking for
something to life for,

01:01:34.900 --> 01:01:36.428 align:middle line:90%
just go get somebody pregnant.

01:01:36.428 --> 01:01:37.228 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

01:01:37.228 --> 01:01:40.252 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

01:01:40.252 --> 01:01:45.032 align:middle line:90%


01:01:45.032 --> 01:01:47.250 align:middle line:90%
Oh, man.

01:01:47.250 --> 01:01:48.810 align:middle line:90%
I've never done that.

01:01:48.810 --> 01:01:50.790 align:middle line:90%
That's an amazing thought.

01:01:50.790 --> 01:01:55.200 align:middle line:84%
It's amazing--
thinking about this now

01:01:55.200 --> 01:02:01.020 align:middle line:84%
makes me want to thank them
and help them understand

01:02:01.020 --> 01:02:04.380 align:middle line:90%
how they helped me survive.

01:02:04.380 --> 01:02:05.970 align:middle line:90%
And they're still pretty young.

01:02:05.970 --> 01:02:08.850 align:middle line:84%
They know their
dad's the cancer guy

01:02:08.850 --> 01:02:13.050 align:middle line:84%
and they know I'm
famous on the internet.

01:02:13.050 --> 01:02:15.720 align:middle line:90%


01:02:15.720 --> 01:02:21.900 align:middle line:84%
But we haven't had really
deep conversations about life

01:02:21.900 --> 01:02:29.160 align:middle line:84%
and cancer and what I was
going through mentally

01:02:29.160 --> 01:02:31.950 align:middle line:84%
and emotionally back
then because feel

01:02:31.950 --> 01:02:35.318 align:middle line:84%
like it's a little heavy
for them at this age.

01:02:35.318 --> 01:02:36.860 align:middle line:84%
But maybe we'll talk
about that soon.

01:02:36.860 --> 01:02:40.020 align:middle line:90%


01:02:40.020 --> 01:02:42.620 align:middle line:84%
One of the speakers
at this conference,

01:02:42.620 --> 01:02:44.730 align:middle line:84%
and I don't remember
who it was, reminded me

01:02:44.730 --> 01:02:46.110 align:middle line:90%
of this quote I've heard before.

01:02:46.110 --> 01:02:50.550 align:middle line:90%
But it was that your children--

01:02:50.550 --> 01:02:54.360 align:middle line:84%
I'm paraphrasing, but it's like,
your children basically teach

01:02:54.360 --> 01:02:57.055 align:middle line:90%
you what's wrong with you.

01:02:57.055 --> 01:02:57.855 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

01:02:57.855 --> 01:03:01.278 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

01:03:01.278 --> 01:03:05.200 align:middle line:90%


01:03:05.200 --> 01:03:07.480 align:middle line:84%
As I was reading and learning
and trying to figure out

01:03:07.480 --> 01:03:10.960 align:middle line:84%
how I could help
myself more, I stumbled

01:03:10.960 --> 01:03:15.910 align:middle line:84%
across visualization and
affirmations and some of it,

01:03:15.910 --> 01:03:21.370 align:middle line:84%
again, I knew because I had read
successful people books, being

01:03:21.370 --> 01:03:24.340 align:middle line:84%
in sales and being
an entrepreneur,

01:03:24.340 --> 01:03:26.380 align:middle line:84%
but had never really
practiced those things.

01:03:26.380 --> 01:03:28.005 align:middle line:84%
Because I always
thought, I don't know.

01:03:28.005 --> 01:03:30.330 align:middle line:84%
They seem hokey and it's
a little bit embarrassing

01:03:30.330 --> 01:03:34.608 align:middle line:84%
to picture myself in front of
a mirror like Stuart Smalley

01:03:34.608 --> 01:03:35.650 align:middle line:90%
on "Saturday Night Live."

01:03:35.650 --> 01:03:38.410 align:middle line:90%


01:03:38.410 --> 01:03:42.070 align:middle line:84%
But I was like,
I don't care now.

01:03:42.070 --> 01:03:43.430 align:middle line:90%
I'll do anything.

01:03:43.430 --> 01:03:47.470 align:middle line:84%
There's nothing that
I am above if it's

01:03:47.470 --> 01:03:50.025 align:middle line:90%
going to help me get well.

01:03:50.025 --> 01:03:51.900 align:middle line:84%
And it started to make
more sense to me, too.

01:03:51.900 --> 01:03:57.910 align:middle line:84%
And I realized that our thoughts
have power and so do our words.

01:03:57.910 --> 01:04:02.420 align:middle line:84%
And so I started speaking
life into my body.

01:04:02.420 --> 01:04:05.470 align:middle line:84%
I started speaking like,
I'm healed, I'm healthy,

01:04:05.470 --> 01:04:08.320 align:middle line:84%
and I'm well, over
and over again.

01:04:08.320 --> 01:04:10.390 align:middle line:90%
I would just speak it out loud.

01:04:10.390 --> 01:04:13.183 align:middle line:84%
And I would think it
throughout the day.

01:04:13.183 --> 01:04:14.600 align:middle line:84%
Your thoughts
create your reality.

01:04:14.600 --> 01:04:17.580 align:middle line:84%
And the Bible says as a
man thinketh, so he is.

01:04:17.580 --> 01:04:22.180 align:middle line:84%
This is a super
famous piece of wisdom

01:04:22.180 --> 01:04:26.110 align:middle line:84%
that has been repeated ad
nauseam in the success world.

01:04:26.110 --> 01:04:28.510 align:middle line:84%
"As a Man Thinketh"
is a very famous book.

01:04:28.510 --> 01:04:30.290 align:middle line:84%
But it's straight
out of Proverbs.

01:04:30.290 --> 01:04:32.370 align:middle line:84%
And so I'm like, as a
man thinks, so he is.

01:04:32.370 --> 01:04:36.100 align:middle line:84%
So I'm like, I'm going to
start thinking, I am healed,

01:04:36.100 --> 01:04:38.050 align:middle line:90%
I'm healthy, I'm well.

01:04:38.050 --> 01:04:40.930 align:middle line:84%
And I just-- over
and over and over.

01:04:40.930 --> 01:04:42.030 align:middle line:90%
So that was a big--

01:04:42.030 --> 01:04:43.795 align:middle line:84%
just like, I'm
healed, I'm healthy,

01:04:43.795 --> 01:04:46.850 align:middle line:90%
I'm well, over and over.

01:04:46.850 --> 01:04:51.400 align:middle line:84%
And then I didn't really
get into deep visualization,

01:04:51.400 --> 01:05:00.490 align:middle line:84%
but I would think about myself
in the future periodically.

01:05:00.490 --> 01:05:03.400 align:middle line:84%
It wasn't a daily
discipline, but just I

01:05:03.400 --> 01:05:06.850 align:middle line:84%
would try to think about
myself in the future as a dad

01:05:06.850 --> 01:05:10.480 align:middle line:84%
and as a granddad and
visualizing myself

01:05:10.480 --> 01:05:12.610 align:middle line:90%
as a grandfather.

01:05:12.610 --> 01:05:18.100 align:middle line:84%
And that was part of, again,
making plans for the future.

01:05:18.100 --> 01:05:20.860 align:middle line:84%
And so whether making
plans and visualization--

01:05:20.860 --> 01:05:23.050 align:middle line:90%
they're interconnected.

01:05:23.050 --> 01:05:27.190 align:middle line:90%
And I feel like it was helpful.

01:05:27.190 --> 01:05:30.250 align:middle line:84%
I know the affirmations
were helpful.

01:05:30.250 --> 01:05:31.300 align:middle line:90%
They help me now.

01:05:31.300 --> 01:05:37.060 align:middle line:84%
I do stupid stuff like, I'm
worthy, I'm smart, I'm capable.

01:05:37.060 --> 01:05:38.950 align:middle line:84%
I have to talk to
myself sometimes.

01:05:38.950 --> 01:05:42.865 align:middle line:84%
Because that doubt creeps
in when you're doing stuff.

01:05:42.865 --> 01:05:44.740 align:middle line:84%
When you're a speaker
and you're around a lot

01:05:44.740 --> 01:05:47.662 align:middle line:84%
of successful people, you tend
to have imposter syndrome where

01:05:47.662 --> 01:05:49.120 align:middle line:84%
you feel like, I
don't belong here,

01:05:49.120 --> 01:05:52.030 align:middle line:84%
these people are all way
better than me, or something.

01:05:52.030 --> 01:05:59.390 align:middle line:84%
And so someone smarter
than me told me, man, you

01:05:59.390 --> 01:06:03.010 align:middle line:84%
got to tell yourself, no,
you deserve to be here.

01:06:03.010 --> 01:06:04.940 align:middle line:90%
You know you are worthy.

01:06:04.940 --> 01:06:05.740 align:middle line:90%
You do belong.

01:06:05.740 --> 01:06:08.980 align:middle line:90%


01:06:08.980 --> 01:06:11.170 align:middle line:90%
This is your time.

01:06:11.170 --> 01:06:12.040 align:middle line:90%
And so yeah.

01:06:12.040 --> 01:06:14.170 align:middle line:90%
So I do some of that kind of--

01:06:14.170 --> 01:06:16.200 align:middle line:84%
I don't look in the
mirror and do it,

01:06:16.200 --> 01:06:17.725 align:middle line:84%
but I just talk to
myself sometimes.

01:06:17.725 --> 01:06:20.350 align:middle line:84%
And sometimes it's out loud and
sometimes it's just in my head,

01:06:20.350 --> 01:06:21.558 align:middle line:90%
