making this dividing line

01:12:29.970 --> 01:12:31.830 align:middle line:84%
in your life between
the essential

01:12:31.830 --> 01:12:33.540 align:middle line:90%
and the non-essential.

01:12:33.540 --> 01:12:36.810 align:middle line:90%
And you realize right away--

01:12:36.810 --> 01:12:38.940 align:middle line:84%
maybe some cancer
patients don't.

01:12:38.940 --> 01:12:44.620 align:middle line:84%
For me, right away, I realized
this much was essential

01:12:44.620 --> 01:12:47.880 align:middle line:90%
and this much was not essential.

01:12:47.880 --> 01:12:53.070 align:middle line:84%
It was like, my wife my family,
my health, roof over my head,

01:12:53.070 --> 01:12:57.300 align:middle line:84%
food, what we call the
basic human necessities,

01:12:57.300 --> 01:13:00.630 align:middle line:90%
Maslow's hierarchy of needs--

01:13:00.630 --> 01:13:02.010 align:middle line:90%
my needs are met.

01:13:02.010 --> 01:13:03.660 align:middle line:90%
I've got the essentials.

01:13:03.660 --> 01:13:06.380 align:middle line:84%
Everything else
doesn't even matter.

01:13:06.380 --> 01:13:08.438 align:middle line:90%
And if I have some of it, great.

01:13:08.438 --> 01:13:09.730 align:middle line:90%
It'd be fun to have more money.

01:13:09.730 --> 01:13:12.690 align:middle line:84%
It'd be fun to be able to
go on a cruise or whatever.

01:13:12.690 --> 01:13:18.660 align:middle line:84%
