And I was actually starting
to turn into a little bit

01:28:41.230 --> 01:28:43.865 align:middle line:90%
of a snob about it.

01:28:43.865 --> 01:28:45.490 align:middle line:84%
But at the same time,
I wanted to live.

01:28:45.490 --> 01:28:48.430 align:middle line:90%


01:28:48.430 --> 01:28:51.410 align:middle line:84%
And I trusted this man
that was helping me.

01:28:51.410 --> 01:28:54.190 align:middle line:84%
And so I was like, well-- and
I knew I was way underweight.

01:28:54.190 --> 01:28:56.440 align:middle line:84%
I looked in the mirror and
I didn't like what I saw.

01:28:56.440 --> 01:28:58.780 align:middle line:84%
So I was like, OK,
I just want to live.

01:28:58.780 --> 01:29:00.880 align:middle line:84%
If you think it's
OK, I'll try it.

01:29:00.880 --> 01:29:02.710 align:middle line:84%
So we added a little
more cooked food,

01:29:02.710 --> 01:29:04.300 align:middle line:90%
a little bit of animal protein.

01:29:04.300 --> 01:29:07.300 align:middle line:84%
And I was able to get back
up to a normal weight range

01:29:07.300 --> 01:29:10.870 align:middle line:84%
and maintain that
diet for years.

01:29:10.870 --> 01:29:14.770 align:middle line:84%
So that was the diet
that for many years

01:29:14.770 --> 01:29:18.248 align:middle line:84%
was my anticancer diet, giant
salads, juicing all day,

01:29:18.248 --> 01:29:20.290 align:middle line:84%
a little bit of cooked
food in my salad at night,

01:29:20.290 --> 01:29:23.230 align:middle line:84%
and occasional serving
of animal protein.

01:29:23.230 --> 01:29:26.230 align:middle line:90%
And now it's been 13 years.

01:29:26.230 --> 01:29:29.770 align:middle line:84%
And once I got past
the five-year mark,

01:29:29.770 --> 01:29:31.780 align:middle line:84%
I started experimenting
with different diets.

01:29:31.780 --> 01:29:33.925 align:middle line:84%
The paleo diet was
getting popular

01:29:33.925 --> 01:29:35.590 align:middle line:90%
and I was interested in it.

01:29:35.590 --> 01:29:37.090 align:middle line:84%
Experimented with
that a little bit.

01:29:37.090 --> 01:29:39.790 align:middle line:84%
Experimented with Weston
Price and the raw milk

01:29:39.790 --> 01:29:43.270 align:middle line:84%
and raw eggs, raw butter,
and the other side

01:29:43.270 --> 01:29:44.860 align:middle line:84%
of raw food eating,
except I never

01:29:44.860 --> 01:29:46.870 align:middle line:90%
got into the raw meat eating.

01:29:46.870 --> 01:29:49.510 align:middle line:84%
But I started investigating
a lot of different diets

01:29:49.510 --> 01:29:52.030 align:middle line:84%
and became obsessed
with healthy cultures

01:29:52.030 --> 01:29:53.990 align:middle line:90%
and healthy populations.

01:29:53.990 --> 01:29:57.070 align:middle line:84%
And I realized that there
are a lot of gurus promoting

01:29:57.070 --> 01:30:02.530 align:middle line:84%
healthy diets, but a lot
of their healthy diet ideas

01:30:02.530 --> 01:30:05.800 align:middle line:84%
were not grounded
in real people.

01:30:05.800 --> 01:30:08.800 align:middle line:84%
They were just
grounded in theory.

01:30:08.800 --> 01:30:13.000 align:middle line:84%
And so the deeper
I dug and the more

01:30:13.000 --> 01:30:16.790 align:middle line:84%
I started to read and research,
I realized, wait a minute.

01:30:16.790 --> 01:30:21.730 align:middle line:84%
We've got healthy, long-living
cultures around the world

01:30:21.730 --> 01:30:24.400 align:middle line:90%
already, established.

01:30:24.400 --> 01:30:26.747 align:middle line:90%
What are they doing?

01:30:26.747 --> 01:30:27.580 align:middle line:90%
How are they eating?

01:30:27.580 --> 01:30:28.480 align:middle line:90%
How are they living?

01:30:28.480 --> 01:30:29.897 align:middle line:84%
And then I found
this amazing book

01:30:29.897 --> 01:30:32.080 align:middle line:84%
called "The Blue Zones,"
which is all about that,

01:30:32.080 --> 01:30:34.930 align:middle line:84%
and another book by John
Robbins, "Healthy at 100."

01:30:34.930 --> 01:30:39.310 align:middle line:84%
And so those books were really
great because again, they--

01:30:39.310 --> 01:30:41.410 align:middle line:84%
"The Blue Zones" is a
National Geographic project.

01:30:41.410 --> 01:30:44.140 align:middle line:84%
And they travel the world
and they found these isolated

01:30:44.140 --> 01:30:47.440 align:middle line:84%
pockets where they had really
high percentages of people

01:30:47.440 --> 01:30:49.300 align:middle line:90%
living past 100.

01:30:49.300 --> 01:30:54.058 align:middle line:84%
And they studied their
diet and lifestyle habits.

01:30:54.058 --> 01:30:56.350 align:middle line:84%
And they realized, wow,
there's a lot of common threads

01:30:56.350 --> 01:30:57.790 align:middle line:84%
all over the world with
these people groups

01:30:57.790 --> 01:30:59.623 align:middle line:84%
even though they're on
different continents.

01:30:59.623 --> 01:31:02.630 align:middle line:90%
Their diet's 95% plant-based.

01:31:02.630 --> 01:31:03.860 align:middle line:90%
So they're not vegans.

01:31:03.860 --> 01:31:05.740 align:middle line:90%
They're not raw vegans.

01:31:05.740 --> 01:31:07.930 align:middle line:84%
But their diet is almost
exclusively plants.

01:31:07.930 --> 01:31:10.980 align:middle line:84%
They might eat meat a few times
a week, a few times a month,

01:31:10.980 --> 01:31:12.700 align:middle line:90%
but it's very low.

01:31:12.700 --> 01:31:15.310 align:middle line:84%
And they have really
good community support.

01:31:15.310 --> 01:31:17.650 align:middle line:84%
And they typically get a lot
of fresh air and sunshine

01:31:17.650 --> 01:31:19.775 align:middle line:84%
because they're poor and
they're walking everywhere

01:31:19.775 --> 01:31:21.130 align:middle line:90%
and they're working outside.

01:31:21.130 --> 01:31:24.260 align:middle line:84%
And when I say
community support,

01:31:24.260 --> 01:31:28.330 align:middle line:84%
they have good, really
strong social structure,

01:31:28.330 --> 01:31:31.090 align:middle line:84%
big, extended families, and
they spend a lot of time

01:31:31.090 --> 01:31:33.070 align:middle line:90%
together as a community.

01:31:33.070 --> 01:31:38.950 align:middle line:84%
And so then I started to read
the science and the studies

01:31:38.950 --> 01:31:41.610 align:middle line:90%
behind those books.

01:31:41.610 --> 01:31:44.705 align:middle line:84%
And it was like, OK,
I now understand.

01:31:44.705 --> 01:31:46.330 align:middle line:84%
These are the people
I want to emulate.

01:31:46.330 --> 01:31:48.280 align:middle line:84%
I don't want to
emulate the guru who

01:31:48.280 --> 01:31:51.760 align:middle line:84%
has some caveman theory
of our healthiest diet,

01:31:51.760 --> 01:31:54.880 align:middle line:84%
that we need to
eat like a caveman.

01:31:54.880 --> 01:31:57.460 align:middle line:84%
I want to emulate the
healthiest people on Earth

01:31:57.460 --> 01:32:01.860 align:middle line:84%
now, that are real,
that we can study,

01:32:01.860 --> 01:32:04.290 align:middle line:84%
that we don't have to
speculate anything about.

01:32:04.290 --> 01:32:07.920 align:middle line:84%
And so that brought
me full circle

01:32:07.920 --> 01:32:10.170 align:middle line:84%
from experimenting
with different things

01:32:10.170 --> 01:32:13.170 align:middle line:84%
and eating a lot more meat
than I had been eating

01:32:13.170 --> 01:32:14.820 align:middle line:90%
when I had cancer and things.

01:32:14.820 --> 01:32:16.500 align:middle line:84%
And I realized,
yeah, you know what?

01:32:16.500 --> 01:32:19.710 align:middle line:84%
My initial cancer diet
was right on the money.

01:32:19.710 --> 01:32:22.450 align:middle line:84%
But with my metabolism, I just
need a little more cooked food

01:32:22.450 --> 01:32:23.250 align:middle line:90%
versus raw.

01:32:23.250 --> 01:32:27.330 align:middle line:84%
So my diet now is
about 98% plant-based.

01:32:27.330 --> 01:32:32.160 align:middle line:84%
And I eat one raw meal a
day and two cooked meals.

01:32:32.160 --> 01:32:34.440 align:middle line:84%
And I basically eat the
same stuff every day.

01:32:34.440 --> 01:32:36.810 align:middle line:90%
I'm a minimalist.

01:32:36.810 --> 01:32:38.685 align:middle line:84%
Breakfast is a giant
bowl of oatmeal

01:32:38.685 --> 01:32:41.760 align:middle line:84%
with tons of fruit in it and
hemp seed, flaxseed, chia seed,

01:32:41.760 --> 01:32:43.570 align:middle line:90%
cinnamon, lots of good stuff.

01:32:43.570 --> 01:32:47.070 align:middle line:84%
Lunch is a huge smoothie, lots
of fruit, 4 cups of berries,

01:32:47.070 --> 01:32:51.600 align:middle line:84%
10 dates, handfuls of spinach
and kale, almonds, walnuts.

01:32:51.600 --> 01:32:54.930 align:middle line:84%
And then dinner is
something my wife makes.

01:32:54.930 --> 01:32:56.410 align:middle line:90%
So dinner, we mix it up.

01:32:56.410 --> 01:32:58.930 align:middle line:84%
So she'll make--
one example that we

01:32:58.930 --> 01:33:00.660 align:middle line:84%
have [INAUDIBLE]
on regular rotation

01:33:00.660 --> 01:33:06.420 align:middle line:84%
would be sweet potato,
black bean quesadillas.

01:33:06.420 --> 01:33:12.360 align:middle line:84%
So it'd be an organic
sprouted tortilla and then

01:33:12.360 --> 01:33:16.110 align:middle line:84%
sweet potatoes and black beans
and lentils and some avocado

01:33:16.110 --> 01:33:18.660 align:middle line:84%
and cilantro and a
little salsa in there.

01:33:18.660 --> 01:33:20.370 align:middle line:90%
And it's delicious.

01:33:20.370 --> 01:33:23.700 align:middle line:84%
It's just so good, my mouth is
watering just talking about it.

01:33:23.700 --> 01:33:26.070 align:middle line:84%
But yeah, she'll just make
a variety of cooked veggies

01:33:26.070 --> 01:33:26.870 align:middle line:90%
for dinner.

01:33:26.870 --> 01:33:30.570 align:middle line:84%
And once or twice a month, if
I have a craving for animal

01:33:30.570 --> 01:33:31.980 align:middle line:90%
protein, I'll have some.

01:33:31.980 --> 01:33:35.070 align:middle line:84%
But it's very
different than back

01:33:35.070 --> 01:33:36.660 align:middle line:84%
when I used to eat
meat every day.

01:33:36.660 --> 01:33:38.760 align:middle line:84%
Because I hear people
say, oh, I just

01:33:38.760 --> 01:33:39.990 align:middle line:90%
couldn't live without meat.

01:33:39.990 --> 01:33:42.460 align:middle line:84%
I have to have
meat with my meal.

01:33:42.460 --> 01:33:48.190 align:middle line:84%
And when you're in that state,
you have a protein addiction.

01:33:48.190 --> 01:33:49.830 align:middle line:84%
You have an animal
protein addiction.

01:33:49.830 --> 01:33:54.330 align:middle line:84%
Your body is adapted to eating
animal protein, this really

01:33:54.330 --> 01:33:56.460 align:middle line:84%
concentrated protein,
three times a day.

01:33:56.460 --> 01:33:59.160 align:middle line:84%
And so yeah, if you stop
doing it, in the short term,

01:33:59.160 --> 01:34:00.390 align:middle line:90%
you feel like crap.

01:34:00.390 --> 01:34:02.770 align:middle line:90%
You have withdrawal from it.

01:34:02.770 --> 01:34:04.980 align:middle line:84%
But once you break
that addiction,

01:34:04.980 --> 01:34:08.250 align:middle line:84%
if you have a craving for
it, it feels very different.

01:34:08.250 --> 01:34:11.070 align:middle line:84%
And it's not every day and it
may not even be every week.

01:34:11.070 --> 01:34:13.040 align:middle line:84%
For me, it's every
maybe few weeks,

01:34:13.040 --> 01:34:16.350 align:middle line:84%
I might feel like I
need a little bit.

01:34:16.350 --> 01:34:18.907 align:middle line:84%
And the cool thing is seeing
all these healthy cultures

01:34:18.907 --> 01:34:21.240 align:middle line:84%
and the way that eat, that's
basically the way they eat,

01:34:21.240 --> 01:34:22.270 align:middle line:90%
too.

01:34:22.270 --> 01:34:23.947 align:middle line:90%
So I feel good about it.

01:34:23.947 --> 01:34:24.747 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

01:34:24.747 --> 01:34:28.086 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

01:34:28.086 --> 01:34:30.950 align:middle line:90%


01:34:30.950 --> 01:34:32.365 align:middle line:90%
Well, spiritual mantra?

01:34:32.365 --> 01:34:34.960 align:middle line:90%


01:34:34.960 --> 01:34:38.710 align:middle line:84%
I'm a pretty minimal,
simple kind of guy.

01:34:38.710 --> 01:34:40.930 align:middle line:90%
And I believe truth is simple.

01:34:40.930 --> 01:34:45.420 align:middle line:84%
And so for me, I believe that
God created the Earth for us

01:34:45.420 --> 01:34:48.130 align:middle line:84%
and that everything we
need comes from the earth.

01:34:48.130 --> 01:34:53.950 align:middle line:84%
And it was that very
simple idea that

01:34:53.950 --> 01:34:58.090 align:middle line:84%
was the foundation of me
adopting this hardcore

01:34:58.090 --> 01:35:02.200 align:middle line:84%
diet of fruits and vegetables,
food from the earth.

01:35:02.200 --> 01:35:03.970 align:middle line:90%
It just made sense to me.

01:35:03.970 --> 01:35:06.760 align:middle line:84%
It was like, I think
truth is simple

01:35:06.760 --> 01:35:08.290 align:middle line:90%
and I'm going to do this.

01:35:08.290 --> 01:35:11.490 align:middle line:90%


01:35:11.490 --> 01:35:13.600 align:middle line:84%
But there was a lot
of fear in my journey.

01:35:13.600 --> 01:35:19.090 align:middle line:84%
And it required me to go
very deep in my faith.

01:35:19.090 --> 01:35:20.800 align:middle line:90%
It was a test of my faith.

01:35:20.800 --> 01:35:23.200 align:middle line:84%
Because faith is
believing in something

01:35:23.200 --> 01:35:27.280 align:middle line:84%
that you don't have
physical evidence of.

01:35:27.280 --> 01:35:31.480 align:middle line:84%
And for me, it was believing
that when I asked God for help

01:35:31.480 --> 01:35:36.340 align:middle line:84%
and I got an answer, that it
was from him, and that if it was

01:35:36.340 --> 01:35:43.330 align:middle line:84%
from him, that if I took this
very different path, that he

01:35:43.330 --> 01:35:45.280 align:middle line:90%
would see me through it.

01:35:45.280 --> 01:35:53.890 align:middle line:84%
And it was a daily struggle
to fight doubt and fear.

01:35:53.890 --> 01:35:58.540 align:middle line:84%
And you can be in fear and
in faith at the same time.

01:35:58.540 --> 01:36:03.220 align:middle line:84%
You can be also fearful,
but moving forward in faith.

01:36:03.220 --> 01:36:05.410 align:middle line:90%
But doubt is the enemy of faith.

01:36:05.410 --> 01:36:06.460 align:middle line:90%
You can't have both.

01:36:06.460 --> 01:36:07.930 align:middle line:90%
They cannot both exist.

01:36:07.930 --> 01:36:11.620 align:middle line:84%
So fighting doubt was a
big part of my daily--

01:36:11.620 --> 01:36:12.810 align:middle line:90%
because doubts creep in.

01:36:12.810 --> 01:36:15.775 align:middle line:84%
And I would just have to catch
myself and be like, I'm just

01:36:15.775 --> 01:36:16.900 align:middle line:90%
going to choose to believe.

01:36:16.900 --> 01:36:18.030 align:middle line:90%
I'm going to do this.

01:36:18.030 --> 01:36:18.970 align:middle line:90%
God, I trust you.

01:36:18.970 --> 01:36:20.770 align:middle line:90%
You're in control.

01:36:20.770 --> 01:36:23.530 align:middle line:90%
Please don't let me die.

01:36:23.530 --> 01:36:25.990 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to do
everything I can do.

01:36:25.990 --> 01:36:27.290 align:middle line:90%
I'm doing everything I can do.

01:36:27.290 --> 01:36:30.420 align:middle line:84%
But at the end of the
day, I know you're--

01:36:30.420 --> 01:36:32.920 align:middle line:84%
I'm choosing to believe
that you're in control.

01:36:32.920 --> 01:36:36.340 align:middle line:84%
I know in my heart, deep down,
you're in control of this.

01:36:36.340 --> 01:36:38.290 align:middle line:90%
And I'm trusting you.

01:36:38.290 --> 01:36:43.410 align:middle line:84%
Because there were many moments
where I just had this thought--

01:36:43.410 --> 01:36:45.110 align:middle line:84%
I'd be my car or
something and I'd

01:36:45.110 --> 01:36:49.407 align:middle line:84%
get a little bit
overwhelmed with fear.

01:36:49.407 --> 01:36:51.490 align:middle line:84%
And I'd just be like, it's
just you and me, Jesus.

01:36:51.490 --> 01:36:52.870 align:middle line:90%
I don't know what else to do.

01:36:52.870 --> 01:36:54.580 align:middle line:90%
I don't have anybody else.

01:36:54.580 --> 01:36:59.200 align:middle line:90%
And so it was just me and Jesus.

01:36:59.200 --> 01:37:00.460 align:middle line:90%
That was it.

01:37:00.460 --> 01:37:01.900 align:middle line:90%
It was all I had.

01:37:01.900 --> 01:37:03.760 align:middle line:84%
As much as my mom loves
me and supported me,

01:37:03.760 --> 01:37:07.090 align:middle line:84%
and of course my wife ended
up becoming a big support,

01:37:07.090 --> 01:37:10.810 align:middle line:84%
you're still very alone
in the cancer journey.

01:37:10.810 --> 01:37:13.870 align:middle line:84%
It's you and your thoughts and
your life and your decisions

01:37:13.870 --> 01:37:16.600 align:middle line:90%
and your future.

01:37:16.600 --> 01:37:21.190 align:middle line:84%
And so it pushed me
very deep into faith.

01:37:21.190 --> 01:37:22.657 align:middle line:90%
I was already a believer.

01:37:22.657 --> 01:37:23.740 align:middle line:90%
I was already a Christian.

01:37:23.740 --> 01:37:31.210 align:middle line:84%
But it was like, OK, I really
got to go deep, deep, and trust

01:37:31.210 --> 01:37:34.540 align:middle line:84%
that God is in control and
that if I put my faith in him,

01:37:34.540 --> 01:37:36.040 align:middle line:90%
that he won't let me down.

01:37:36.040 --> 01:37:38.300 align:middle line:90%
And he didn't.

01:37:38.300 --> 01:37:41.290 align:middle line:84%
And what I encourage
people to do--

01:37:41.290 --> 01:37:43.270 align:middle line:84%
if they don't believe
there's a God--

01:37:43.270 --> 01:37:47.020 align:middle line:84%
and I think when you have
cancer, you're much more open.

01:37:47.020 --> 01:37:49.520 align:middle line:84%
You're confronted
with death and so--

01:37:49.520 --> 01:37:52.060 align:middle line:84%
but if you don't believe or you
don't know or your not sure,

01:37:52.060 --> 01:37:53.490 align:middle line:90%
just reach out.

01:37:53.490 --> 01:37:55.180 align:middle line:90%
That's it.

01:37:55.180 --> 01:37:58.270 align:middle line:84%
You don't have to go
to church tomorrow.

01:37:58.270 --> 01:38:01.900 align:middle line:84%
Just reach out and
ask, are you there?

01:38:01.900 --> 01:38:03.610 align:middle line:90%
Reveal yourself.

01:38:03.610 --> 01:38:04.520 align:middle line:90%
I need help.

01:38:04.520 --> 01:38:08.620 align:middle line:84%
I'm-- just a sincere
prayer, like, OK,

01:38:08.620 --> 01:38:11.850 align:middle line:90%
you've got my attention.

01:38:11.850 --> 01:38:13.540 align:middle line:90%
Here I am.

01:38:13.540 --> 01:38:14.560 align:middle line:90%
Just speak to me.

01:38:14.560 --> 01:38:17.560 align:middle line:90%
Show me people in my life--

01:38:17.560 --> 01:38:19.300 align:middle line:90%
I don't know.

01:38:19.300 --> 01:38:22.810 align:middle line:84%
And when you do that, amazing
things happen, when you ask.

01:38:22.810 --> 01:38:24.730 align:middle line:84%
But you also have
to be willing--

01:38:24.730 --> 01:38:28.570 align:middle line:84%
you have to put your
little antenna up.

01:38:28.570 --> 01:38:31.060 align:middle line:90%
Because you can't just say--

01:38:31.060 --> 01:38:33.100 align:middle line:84%
God never really answers
prayer-- usually,

01:38:33.100 --> 01:38:39.820 align:middle line:84%
it's not just like, can I have
a pony, blip, like, oh, hey.

01:38:39.820 --> 01:38:40.990 align:middle line:90%
He uses people.

01:38:40.990 --> 01:38:42.320 align:middle line:90%
God works through people.

01:38:42.320 --> 01:38:46.030 align:middle line:84%
And so if you're
asking for help,

01:38:46.030 --> 01:38:48.460 align:middle line:84%
then you have to really
have your eyes open

01:38:48.460 --> 01:38:52.540 align:middle line:84%
and be looking for the answer
to come to you, and then

01:38:52.540 --> 01:38:53.560 align:middle line:90%
not just--

01:38:53.560 --> 01:38:54.977 align:middle line:84%
if something comes,
you can't just

01:38:54.977 --> 01:38:56.980 align:middle line:84%
be like, oh, it's
just a coincidence,

01:38:56.980 --> 01:38:58.090 align:middle line:90%
and then throw it out.

01:38:58.090 --> 01:39:02.680 align:middle line:84%
Because you just totally
hijacked maybe a huge blessing.

01:39:02.680 --> 01:39:05.900 align:middle line:84%
If that book had come to
me and I'd just been like,

01:39:05.900 --> 01:39:11.550 align:middle line:84%
I don't know, who knows what
my life would have been like?

01:39:11.550 --> 01:39:14.560 align:middle line:84%
Or if I had let the
doubt overtake my faith--

01:39:14.560 --> 01:39:18.340 align:middle line:84%
because people
were pushing doubt.

01:39:18.340 --> 01:39:21.050 align:middle line:84%
They were really feeding this
doubt, like, don't do this.

01:39:21.050 --> 01:39:21.850 align:middle line:90%
It's a mistake.

01:39:21.850 --> 01:39:23.530 align:middle line:90%
This doesn't work.

01:39:23.530 --> 01:39:25.660 align:middle line:90%
Got to do what the doctor says.

01:39:25.660 --> 01:39:30.530 align:middle line:84%
And if I had really let
the doubt take over,

01:39:30.530 --> 01:39:33.120 align:middle line:90%
then I'd probably be dead.

01:39:33.120 --> 01:39:36.600 align:middle line:84%
I wouldn't have my
beautiful girls.

01:39:36.600 --> 01:39:38.115 align:middle line:84%
Who knows what
would have happened?

01:39:38.115 --> 01:39:40.890 align:middle line:84%
But that's where the rubber
meets the road because--

01:39:40.890 --> 01:39:42.720 align:middle line:90%
there's a verse in James.

01:39:42.720 --> 01:39:45.990 align:middle line:84%
And it says faith
without works is dead.

01:39:45.990 --> 01:39:49.050 align:middle line:90%
And works means action.

01:39:49.050 --> 01:39:52.510 align:middle line:84%
And so you prove your
faith by your actions,

01:39:52.510 --> 01:39:56.640 align:middle line:84%
like I believe this, therefore
I'm doing something about it,

01:39:56.640 --> 01:40:00.792 align:middle line:84%
like, I believe this
chair will hold me up;

01:40:00.792 --> 01:40:02.250 align:middle line:84%
I'm willing to put
my weight on it.

01:40:02.250 --> 01:40:08.970 align:middle line:90%


01:40:08.970 --> 01:40:10.980 align:middle line:84%
People get confused
about what faith is.

01:40:10.980 --> 01:40:12.627 align:middle line:84%
It's not just
believing something.

01:40:12.627 --> 01:40:14.460 align:middle line:84%
It's believing something
so much that you're

01:40:14.460 --> 01:40:16.710 align:middle line:84%
willing to stake
your life on it.

01:40:16.710 --> 01:40:22.500 align:middle line:84%
You're willing to take
action and with the hope

01:40:22.500 --> 01:40:25.360 align:middle line:84%
that your action will produce
that thing that you have faith

01:40:25.360 --> 01:40:26.160 align:middle line:90%
for.

